title: chewy cheese bars
directions: Mix the first 3 items together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dieter's tuna fish salad
directions: Mix tuna and salad dressing in mixing bowl.
Chill, then serve.
Low-fat crackers go great with this salad.

title: pecan drops
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then fold in egg whites.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie
sheet
and bake in slow oven at 325° to 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onion and celery together.
Mix oil, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over beans.

title: sloppy joe onion rings
directions: Place onion rings in a well greased baking dish.
Sprinkle ground beef evenly over onion rings.
Pour sloppy joe sauce evenly over beef.
Bake according to onion rings bag directions.
Serve hot.

title: herbed baked eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 4 greased ramekin dishes (small souffle) with ham.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, yogurt and mustard.
Mix together chives and parsley.
Stir 1/2 of herb mixture and 1/4 cup cheese into egg mixture.
Spoon into dishes and top with remaining cheese and herbs.
Bake until golden brown and set, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients; beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and margarine.
Stir in nuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Steam or poach chicken breasts until they are barely done. When well chilled, slice thinly.
Cook broccoli tender-crisp. Arrange broccoli evenly over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Distribute chicken slices evenly over the broccoli. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry and most of the Cheddar cheese and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Add the rest of the cheese to the cooled buttered crumbs and sprinkle over the casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) at least 45 minutes until the casserole is bubbly and heated through.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, combine thawed ground beef, salsa, eggs, chips, salt and cheese. Mix well. Grease two loaf pans and divide mixture evenly in the two pans. Pat firmly into shape. Bake for 1 hour. Remove and let stand for 10 to 15 minutes. Cut into slices. Serve with extra salsa, if desired. Makes 10 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add dry ingredients. Add zucchini.
Grease bread pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Check after 1 hour.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; place in casserole dish.
Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper, then add cooked rice.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce and paste.
Fill each green pepper with mixture and top each one with cheese.
Add spaghetti sauce after you filled peppers and placed in dish.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 1 1/2 hours or until green peppers are done.

title: orange jubilee
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process on high speed until well mixed.
Serve immediately.
(Great on a hot summer day!)
Yield: 5 servings.

title: potatoes and onions
directions: Slice potatoes and onions.
Arrange in a pan greased with oil. Add salt, pepper, onion powder, parsley and bread crumbs.
Pour a small amount of olive oil over potatoes and onions, add a little water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: honey-baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken (skins can be removed).
Melt the margarine (or butter or oil) in a shallow baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll the chicken pieces in this mixture, then arrange in a single layer in the same pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the remaining ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup water and nuts.
Grease and flour three 1 pound coffee cans and fill 2/3 full.
Bake, without lids, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool and store in cans with lids on.
May freeze.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, celery and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining canned onions and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to instructions on box.
Break eggs into measuring cup and beat until blended.
Pour in enough milk to make 1 cup.
When grits are done, cut up cheese and butter; drop into hot grits.
Stir until melted completely.
Let cool for several minutes and then pour in egg mixture.
Stir until all ingredients are blended.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Crushed corn flakes can be added to the top before baking.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a saucepan. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Beat in egg to form gel.
Add sugar.
Press into buttered loaf pan. Refrigerate until cold.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Combine rhubarb, apples and strawberries; spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over rhubarb mixture.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in brown sugar and oats.
Sprinkle over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Mix pudding with milk and fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Grind Oreos in food processor or blender until consistency of dirt.
Layer in a foil-lined clay flowerpot.
Begin with Oreos and end with Oreos.
You may decorate with a silk flower (stem wrapped in Saran Wrap.)
Enjoy!

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; let cool.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Simmer carrots and onions until tender.
Add potatoes and chicken broth and simmer 30 minutes. Add broccoli and parsley. Take out about half of potatoes and carrots and blend together with mixer to thicken.
Add cheddar cheese until melted.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Beat eggs; add sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper, cream, vinegar and mustard.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and mayonnaise.

title: boo's beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook for about 4 hours on low in crock-pot.

title: hazel's hassenpfeffer(rabbit)
directions: Skin, dress, draw and clean hare.
Cut meat from bones.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add bacon, carrots, bay leaf, cloves, garlic, salt, pepper, mustard seed, onion, mushrooms and hare meat.
Brown well.
Add 1 cup water or vinegar.
Cover and simmer until tender, about an hour.
Add cream; mix well and serve.
Use young rabbits and hares weighing 2 to 3 pounds.
Do not eat those with unpleasant odors.
They should be drawn and cleaned as soon as possible after killing, but need not be skinned until time to cook.
We used cottontail rabbits; never did have to raise rabbits, as we always found them around the hay fields.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Combine sherbet, punch and sugar.
Mix until sherbet is well blended.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Punch can be served from a punch bowl or poured directly into tall glasses.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 3 to 4 layers.

title: bake and breaded chicken
directions: Mix cheese and bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in salad dressing and coat with crumbs. Let stand for 10-15 mins. Place on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 375° for 50-60 mins.

title: sue's fudge(never fail)
directions: Melt in microwave, butter and chocolate chips.
Blend powdered sugar and eggs.
Add chocolate chips and butter mixture to powdered sugar.
Add pecans.
Work fast.
Pour into 10-inch greased and buttered baking dish.
Delicious!

title: sunday special
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, press hamburger on bottom. Sprinkle chopped onion on top, then spread can of soup over all. Place frozen Tater Tots in a row on top to cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil cookie sheet with liquid vegetable oil.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir in other ingredients. Spoon by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Turn off oven.
Place cookies into oven and leave at least 2 hours or overnight.
Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: microwave fudge(sucre a creme)
directions: Combine.
In microwave-proof baking dish, microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Stir.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: grilled hamburgers
directions: Put beef into large bowl.
Add onions, seasonings and eggs; blend mixture well with fork and form into 12 large hamburgers. Cook patties on greased grill until done.
Serve on hamburger buns with choices of "extras."
(If you prefer, divide the recipe in half for only 6 burgers.)

title: sinful german chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 2 eggs and butter and press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with pecans and coconut.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until golden and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: bacon and filling balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients as for any filling.
Lay 2 bacon strips crisscross on wax paper.
With hands, form bread mixture into balls about size of fist and lay on bacon strips.
Fold bacon around filling and fasten with toothpick, if desired.
Lay side by side in pie plate or shallow baking dish and bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.
(Balls can also be put on broiler pan to bake so fat drains off.)

title: lime punch
directions: Mix ginger ale and pineapple juice; chill.
Stir in ice cream and sherbet about 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 25.

title: hummus bi tahini
directions: Blend all ingredients in a food processor to a creamy paste. Add water or more lemon juice if dip feels too thick.
Pour into serving dishes.
Garnish with whole chickpeas and fresh parsley.

title: cream caramels
directions: Sprinkle nuts in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Mix sugar, corn syrup, butter and half of cream in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in rest of cream gradually. Continue stirring as mixture thickens and cook to 250° or until a little drop in cold water forms a hard ball.
Remove from heat and pour over nuts in pan.
When cold, cut into squares.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Add celery, onion and olives.
Add eggs, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Toss together.
Refrigerate as soon as possible.
This salad can be made a day in advance.
Don't forget to drain broccoli after cooking and to use only mayonnaise in this salad.

title: breakfast before(great for overnight guests.)
directions: Beat eggs with milk and spices.
Layer in pan:
bread cubes, ham and cheese egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave cracker jack
directions: Pop the popcorn, then put this popcorn in a large brown paper bag.
Mix together in a 4-cup glass measuring cup the butter, syrup, brown sugar, salt and peanuts.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir together well and immediately pour over the popped corn.
Shake bag well.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and microwave again.
Shake one last time and pour out on a cookie sheet to cool.
Break apart and enjoy!

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix very well.
Chill.
Form into balls and dip in melted chocolate.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix according to directions on box; let cake
cool.
Do
the
same	for pudding.
In a large punch bowl, crumble
cake mixture, spread half of pudding, pie filling, pineapple
and Cool Whip.
Crumble the other half of cake and layer remaining ingredients.
Top with nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: Salt chicken; cover in flour.
Brown in oil.
Drain.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken in skillet.
Cover.
Let simmer for 30 minutes until chicken is tender.

title: surprise soup
directions: Brown meat; drain and rinse with warm water to remove all fat. Return meat to pan with onion and cook until onion is tender. Add other ingredients and cook, covered, for 30 minutes or until thick.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix the bananas and eggs in a bowl.
Put the remaining ingredients in a bowl; add to first mixture.
Can add 1/2 cup chopped nuts; stir well.
Put in buttered bread pan (9 x 5-inch). Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Melt in pan 4 tablespoons butter.
Add brown sugar, ginger and caraway seed.
Pour over carrots and serve.

title: sweet sliced pickles
directions: Soak whole cucumbers unpeeled in 1 gallon salt water.
(Put enough salt in water to float an egg.)
Cover cucumbers with brine water.
Soak for 48 hours.
Take out of brine and rinse good. Slice cucumbers and add 1 small box alum to each gallon of water. Soak 24 hours.
Pour water off and put white vinegar and turmeric. Soak 24 hours, then drain and rinse.
Let stand in ice water an hour or so, then in a churn, put a layer cucumber, a layer of sugar until all cucumbers are in churn.
Add pickling spices tied in a rag.
(I put 3 bags with a teaspoon spice in each bag.)
Get them in under pickles.
Keep adding sugar so pickles are under juice. Keep in churn until used up.

title: perked punch
directions: Put the pineapple juice, cranberry juice and water in the bottom of a 30-cup coffeepot.
Put the brown sugar, salt, cloves and cinnamon sticks in the basket.
Perk normal length of time for coffee maker.
You may keep any left over in refrigerator and heat as needed.
(Be sure to shake or stir each time before use.)
This makes the house smell so good!
Excellent for Christmas.
Serves 30.

title: the good soup
directions: In a large saucepan, fry onion in 3 tablespoons butter until golden.
Add vegetables, salt, paprika and boiling water.
Bring to a boil and simmer until veggies are tender (around 20 minutes). Mash with potato masher; melt 4 tablespoons butter in saucepan. Blend in flour and let mixture bubble.
Remove from heat and add milk and bouillon cubes.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper; add veggies and heat through.
This soup can be served cold.
Bacon and cheese enhances the flavor.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients as mixing a cake.
When it is mixed well, add the raisins and nuts.
Bake in coffee cans, greased and lightly floured.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix brown sugar, chili sauce and beans together.
Lay bacon across the top.
Bake for 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: bridal shower punch
directions: Mix punch and pineapple juice. Freeze. Remove from freezer and thaw to a slush. Add Sprite just before serving.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes slices in boiling water, just until tender. Drain.
Then place slices in a greased 8-inch square baking dish. Pour cheese sauce and Ranch Dressing over potatoes.
Cover with foil, bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until bubbly. Garnish with green onions and crumbled bacon.
Serves 4-6.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken until thin.
Top 1 chicken breast with 1 slice of cheese, 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese.
Top with chicken breast.
Salt and pepper; dip in beaten egg and milk mixture. Coat with flour.
Dip again in egg mixture and coat with mixture of bread crumbs and crushed chips.
Fry in butter until brown and tender, turning once.
May be served with butter sauce, cheese sauce or Hollandaise sauce.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar, and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, and salt.
Combine mixtures.
Chill dough, then roll into walnut size balls and place on cookie sheet. Flatten & criss-cross the tops with fork.
Bake 10-12 mins on 375°.

title: island chicken
directions: Flour and season skinless, boneless chicken breasts.
Brown in skillet sprayed with cooking spray.
Remove to casserole.

title: tortillas appetizers
directions: Assembly line style, lay tortillas out on table.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together; spread on each tortilla.
Sprinkle chilies, olives and Cheddar on tortillas.
Roll each tortilla tightly and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Chill and cut.
Eat plain or dip in picante sauce.

title: almond puff
directions: Cut softened margarine into flour.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture and mix with fork.
Roll into a ball and divide in half.
On ungreased cookie sheet, pat each half into a 12 x 13-inch strip, about 3 inches apart.
In medium saucepan, heat butter and water to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and stir in extract and flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball in pan; about 1 minute.
Remove from heat, add eggs, one at a time, beat until smooth.
Divide in half, spread over strips; make sure to cover strips with batter.

title: cottage cheese custard pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Can use mixer.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg and/or cinnamon.
Bake at 450° for approximately 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake approximately 25 minutes longer (until center of pie puffs).

title: shells and grapes
directions: While pasta is cooking, mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and garlic powder.
Toss Blue cheese with warm pasta.
Add mayonnaise mixture until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: never fail pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, flour, salt and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover pastry edges with foil to prevent overbrowning.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish, spread 1 cup of sauce.
Layer noodles and cheeses.
Repeat.
Place remaining noodles on top. Add remaining sauce, then cheeses.
Leave uncovered and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown and bubbling.
Let lasagna sit for 10 to 15 minutes and then cut into squares.

title: chili lovers only
directions: In a large pot with 4 cans tomato sauce, brown meat, onions, garlic, green pepper, using 2 cups of water and rinse all the cans.
Stir occasionally with lid on for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Stir. Heat on low until desired thickness, about 1 more hour.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter, vanilla and water; take off heat. Mix in peanut butter and oatmeal.
Place in clumps on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: On each slice of ham, place several green beans or asparagus. Roll up and secure with toothpicks. Place, folded side down, in shallow baking pan. Make sauce by melting butter in saucepan. Add flour and mix well. Gradually add milk and bring to a boil. Stir until thick. Add seasonings and cheese. Pour over rolls and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: jacks dip
directions: Mix well. Serve with vegetables.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Pour this mixture over cake as soon as you take it from oven. Let cool in pan for 20 minutes. Remove; wrap in foil for a day or two.

title: world's simplest candy
directions: Place chocolate chips in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave on High for 1 or 2 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking until melted.
Stir in the nuts or dried fruits (or a combination of them).
Drop the mixture by the teaspoon onto a waxed paper lined baking sheet and refrigerate until firm.
Store at a cool temperature.
Makes about 15 candies.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain, crumble and set aside.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Stir in brown sugar and vinegar; simmer 5 minutes.
Combine onion mixture with beans. Cook in crock-pot for 8 hours on low or bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Top with bacon.
Serves 16.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables and combine in large bowl.
Stir together the salt, pepper, oil, sugar and vinegar until dissolved. Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight.
Stir several times before serving.

title: honey party mix
directions: Melt oleo and a little over 1/2 cup honey.
Stir into mix. Put mix into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Stir 2 times.
Transfer to wax paper.
Let cool.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Drain can of whole tomatoes and retain juice.
Mix together 2 tablespoons of juice from the tomatoes and 1 tablespoon juice from the peppers.
Add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Add 3 chopped tomatoes and finely chopped peppers and liquid mixture to melted cheese.
Mix well.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Beat eggs, milk and pumpkin mix together.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top pumpkin mix.
Pour nuts and melted butter over all.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: scripture cake
directions: Melt Jeremiah 6 in heavy skillet over low heat.
Continue cooking until syrup is deep amber.
Add Genesis 24; cook until syrup is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add Genesis 18 and stir until melted.
Cool.
Makes approximately 1 1/4 cups syrup.

title: wheaties cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Finish mixing by hand.
Form into walnut size balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: collard greens
directions: Place collards in large bunch, cut up and wash very good.
Add cooking oil.
Add large ham hocks and sugar.
Add salt (in large pot).
Add greens.
Cook for 2 or 3 hours or until very tender. Serve hot.

title: potato basket
directions: You will need a 4-inch strainer for this recipe.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except last two (soup and chips); put in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Spread evenly with chicken soup; bake at 320° for 20 minutes.
Add crumbled chips; return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix preceding together; bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tennessee pride hash brown casserole
directions: Cook sausage. Drain. In bowl, mix cheese, soup, sour cream, French onion dip, peppers, salt and pepper. Fold in hash browns. Mix well. Spread 1/2 of hash brown mixture over bottom of greased 9 x 13 dish. Add half of sausage. Repeat layering. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Put margarine in saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and celery salt.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange layer of carrots, then layer of cheese slices until both are used up with carrots on top.
Pour sauce.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini goodies
directions: Slice thin the unpeeled zucchini.
Beat eggs and add all ingredients, except zucchini.
Mix well.
Add sliced zucchini.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken broth, 4 cups broccoli, onion and thyme.
Bring to boil and cook 20 minutes.
Put this in blender 1/2 at a time and blend; set aside.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown sausage
and ground beef; drain.	Place rye bread on cookie sheet
(sprayed
with Pam) and place cheese slice on bread, sausage, ground
beef
and	seasonings placed on top of cheese. Bake at 400° until bubbly.	Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter an 8-inch square casserole.
Thaw broccoli in sieve over bowl to catch liquid.
Mix soup and onions. Stir in 1/4 cup liquid drained from broccoli.
Sprinkle 1/2 of broccoli in casserole.
Top with 1/2 of soup mixture, 1/2 of stuffing mix and 1/2 of melted butter.
Repeat this twice.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Grease sides and bottom of each layer pan.
Makes 3 layers. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and add Ranch dressing to taste.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: risotto
directions: Lightly brown rice and onion in shortening.
Bring soup to a boil. Add rice, onion, bay leaf, cloves and thyme. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook, covered, on low heat until rice is tender.
Add cheese just before serving.
Serve with chicken.

title: turnips
directions: Peel turnips and chop.
Boil until tender, 45 minutes; drain. Use butter generously.
Add sugar and pepper.
A delicious vegetable.

title: crispix sweet minglers
directions: Melt chips over low heat in large pot, stirring constantly until melted.
Stir in peanut butter and peanuts (optional) until well mixed.
Pour cereal into mixture and carefully stir until all pieces are covered with chocolate.

title: mom's hickory nut cake
directions: Cream, until fluffy, the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth and then add stiffly beaten egg whites and nuts.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Add onion and cook over medium heat until tender.
Remove from heat and blend in flour, salt, paprika, mustard, m.s.g. and Worcestershire sauce.
Add 1 cup heavy cream. Simmer sauce 5 minutes.
Add to well drained green beans.
Add cheese on top and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake in shallow 1-quart baking dish until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and sharp cheese together until well blended.
Add onion, green pepper and pimiento.
Mix together well.
Form into a ball and roll into chopped pecans.

title: country ribs with sauerkraut
directions: To make roast easier to carve, have butcher cut between rib bones and lengthwise down center of ribs, cutting the loin into halves.
These rib bones will have plenty of meat on them. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.

title: beef-cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into form of a ball and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: artichoke rounds
directions: Cut bread in 3-inch rounds.
Spread artichokes to drain.
Mix rest of ingredients and top with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add paprika for color.

title: pineapple sandwich spread
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Cream with egg, pineapple and lemon. Cook until thick.
When cool, add 1/2 cup mayonnaise.

title: peanut butter meltway cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil 2 sticks butter, water and 3 tablespoons cocoa.
While hot, add flour mixture.
Add eggs, 2 tablespoons vanilla and sour cream.
Mix and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: turnips au gratin
directions: Place turnips in boiling water.
Add salt and sugar; cover and cook 12 minutes.
Drain.
In saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Blend in flour, salt and pepper; remove from heat and blend in the milk.
Return to heat and cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add cheese.
In a casserole dish, layer alternately turnips and cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spinach dip or sandwich spread
directions: Thaw spinach, then mix with remaining ingredients and chill. Either use as a dip or spread on bread.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain the grease off.
Break your chips up in a bowl.
Add your tomato, onion and lettuce.
Mix your dressing.
Add hamburger meat and cheese together.
Cover and let set 30 minutes before you eat it.

title: strawberry icebox pie
directions: Put marshmallows in double boiler. Add 2 tablespoons of the strawberry juice. Cook until marshmallows are dissolved.
Mix strawberries and marshmallows thoroughly.
Chill about 2 hours. Fold in whipped cream to marshmallow mixture and pour into pastry shell. Chill until firm.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Chop tender stems and flower heads of broccoli and cauliflower.
Add onion and seasonings.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves; garnish with sliced pimento stuffed olives.

title: tofu and pork hash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into oiled casserole and bake in oven at 350° to 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zuppa inglese
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Pour into 2 greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Prepare both packages of pudding mix using half the milk called for on package.
Cover and chill.
Beat cream until stiff, fold in pudding.
Divide in half, set aside.
Stir coffee granules into hot water; cool.
Fold into half of pudding mixture.
Split each cake layer.
Place bottom layer on cake plate and brush with 1 tablespoon rum.
Spread 1/2 of coffee-flavored pudding over rum.
Top with second layer, brush with 1 tablespoon rum.
Spread about 1/4 of plain pudding over rum. Third layer of cake, brush with 1 tablespoon rum.
Spread remaining coffee pudding over rum.
Fourth layer of cake, brush with 1 tablespoon rum, frost top and sides of cake with rest of plain pudding.
Sprinkle top with shaved chocolate.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: nightwalker freezer jam
directions: Stir together fruit and sugar and allow to stand for 1 hour. Boil together pectin and water, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Add to berry mixture.
Pour into clean jars; cover with cheesecloth and let stand 48 hours.
Seal with lids and freeze until ready to use.

title: eggless raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in the 2 cups of water for 15 minutes.
Add while hot the water and sherry; do not stir.
Add salt, ginger, cinnamon, baking soda and flour.
Stir this mixture well.
Bake in large pan (lightly greased) at 375° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in boiling water; cool.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg, applesauce and cooled water and soda mixture. Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: 2 to 3 pound english cut roast
directions: Marinate roast 8 to 12 hours. Rub meat tenderizer into roast twice on each side. Slow broil 45 minutes to 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat sugar and eggs.
Add oil and vanilla. Mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg; gradually add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool on a wire rack.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas well and mix with beaten egg.
Add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Melt butter and add to banana mixture.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients and add to banana mixture.
Bake in a greased 5 x 9-inch pan (2 pound loaf pan) or 2 to 3 smaller loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If using smaller pans, bake 40 minutes.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening; add brown sugar a little at a time; beat well.
Add granulated sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend all together well.
Use hands to form balls.
Put on wax paper.
In double boiler, melt chocolate use large meat fork to drop peanut butter balls into chocolate and put on wax paper and chill.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook onion and celery in water for 5 minutes. Add meat and cook until it changes color. Add other ingredients and cook 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Sift together
cake
mix
and
pudding.
Make a well in center of
the
dry mixture.
Add everything except chocolate chips; mix together.
Stir chips in with a spatula.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for one hour.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Boil the sweet potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel and mash.
Add all ingredients, except egg whites.
Mix well and then fold in egg whites.
Bake at 400° until the sides and top brown. Serve hot.

title: chocolate nut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup chips with margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add biscuit mix, sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and remaining chips.
Turn into well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: carrots lyonnaise
directions: Pare and cut carrots into julienne strips. Cook in bouillon, covered, for 10 minutes. Melt butter. Add onions and cook, covered, for 15 minutes. Stir occasionally. Stir in next 4 ingredients. Bring to boil. Add carrots and stock. Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes. Add pinch of sugar. Serve.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine cream cheese, sour cream, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Beat until fluffy. Stir
in onion and dried beef (and chopped green pepper if you like).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: favorite carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water, about 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain well.
Place carrots, celery, green pepper, onion and celery seed in a large shallow dish; toss lightly and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan, mixing well.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Pour over vegetables; cover and chill 8 to 10 hours or overnight. Yield:
6 servings.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, 1 1/2 cups of the milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until thick and creamy, 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend remaining 1/2 cup milk and egg.
Stir into rice mixture.
Add raisins.
Cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Spoon into serving dishes or oblong glass dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Use nonstick cookie sheet or wax paper. Combine flour, baking soda and salt. In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat sugars and butter until creamy, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula. Beat in vanilla, then eggs one at a time; beat well. At low speed, gradually add flour mixture and beat just until blended, occasionally scraping bowl. With spoon, stir in oats and raisins. Drop dough about 2-inches apart onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake cookies 11 to 13 minutes or until tops are golden brown. Cool for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: jean fuller's golden fruit punch
directions: Boil together the water and sugar; let cool.
Mix the juices and bananas in the blender.
Mix with syrup.
Pour into bowls or ice cube trays; freeze.
One hour before serving, put frozen punch in bowl and add the 7-Up.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, evaporated milk and chilies and heat.
Add chicken. Grate cheese.
Layer tortillas, meat and cheese in baking dish. Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa and salt. Add milk, vanilla and shortening. Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Mix brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over entire batter and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese soup - south dakota style
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, parsley flakes, bouillon cube and salt and pepper. Mix well, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, mixing well, and add this to the vegetables.
Cook until thickened.
Add Velveeta cheese, stir until melted.

title: million dollar cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, egg and vanilla, then dry ingredients. Roll dough into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip in sugar and press down with glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion and cheese.
Mix together the salad dressing, salt and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Add bread cubes; mix well.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds or crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until cheese bubbles through.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix
sugar,
yolks,
Crisco and salt.
Mix well and add buttermilk,
soda,
lemon
extract
and flour. Blend well then fold
in 6 egg whites, beaten stiff.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in tube pan at 350°.
This may be eaten like it is or you may put your favorite icing on it.

title: baked squash and cranberries
directions: Cook the squash, covered, in the salt and water in a large saucepan over high heat until soft, about 15 minutes.
Drain well; let stand in a colander for at least 30 minutes or press down with your hand to force out most of the liquid.
Puree the pulp in a food processor or put through a food mill; it should yield about 4 cups.
Add the eggs, butter, sugar, salt and pepper.
Blend thoroughly.
Fold the cranberries into the mixture.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart baking dish or two smaller ones.
Top with grated nutmeg and bake in a preheated 350° oven until golden and does not shake in the middle when jiggled, about 45 minutes for one casserole, 30 minutes for two.
Yields 8 servings.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Cut bread dough into walnut size pieces and roll in pudding mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch or tube pan and sprinkle any remaining mixture over top.
Pour melted margarine over the top and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bacon bits.
Chill.
Just before serving, sprinkle bacon bits over the salad.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: tex-mex cheesy chicken
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir onion, celery, and garlic in oil over medium heat until onion is translucent, about 5 minutes. Add chicken; cook and stir until chicken is no longer pink. Add chicken broth; bring to a boil. Add potatoes; cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are soft, stirring occasionally. Return to boiling. Dissolve gravy mix in milk; stir in boiling mixture. Add cheese, salsa, and green chilies. Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Makes 8 servings.

title: creamed onions
directions: Cook onions, covered, in a large amount of boiling, salted water until tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain.

title: eggplant salad(turkey)
directions: With toothpick, prick eggplant in several places.
Place on rack in 400° oven.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours, turning once.
Pour corn oil in small porcelain bowl or platter.
When eggplant is cooked, peel while hot; mash finely in small sections on wooden board. Immerse eggplant in oil; add lemon juice to mashed eggplant to prevent darkening.
Add yogurt, garlic and salt; mix well.
Smooth top and garnish with sliced tomato, olives and parsley.
Yields 5 servings.

title: mother's corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and flour.
Add remaining ingredients, ending with beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: texas chili(extra hot)
directions: Crush hot chili peppers.
Remove stems and seeds from ancho peppers.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place all peppers in a blender container.
Cover; blend until ground.
In a large saucepan, brown half of the meat in hot oil.
With a slotted spoon, remove meat and set aside.
Add remaining meat, onion, garlic, cumin and ground chili peppers.
Cook until meat is brown.
Return all meat to saucepan.
Stir in beef broth, water and oregano.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve the chili with hot, cooked pinto beans.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding mix as directed on package using 1 1/2 cups unsweetened pineapple juice for the liquid instead of milk.
Cool. Fold in fruit.
Put in glass serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Apples are optional and should be added shortly before serving if used.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in 2-quart bowl. Microwave 30 to 35 minutes on High or until a small amount dropped in very cold water forms a soft ball (240°).
Stir in peanuts and salt.
Microwave 9 to 12 minutes on High, or until a small amount dropped in very cold water separates into hard, brittle threads (290°).
Immediately stir in butter and soda.
Mix well.
Spread evenly and thinly on large buttered cookie sheet.
Cool, lifting occasionally with spatula to prevent sticking.
Break into pieces when cool.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: stuffed spinach shells
directions: Prepare shells and spinach as label directs.
Pour spinach into large bowl; cool slightly.
Add Ricotta, Mozzarella, salt and pepper.
Stuff each shell with mixture.
Arrange in casserole; spoon spaghetti sauce on and around shells to cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, salt and butter thoroughly.
Beat the egg, lemon rind and vanilla into creamed mixture until light and fluffy.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Gradually stir into creamed ingredients.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into fancy shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 9 to 10 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Store in airtight container. Yields about 7 dozen cookies.

title: mexican food
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add tomato sauce, soup and taco seasoning to the hamburger and stir to a boil.
Line bottom of 9 x 13 in. baking dish with broken tortilla chips.
Sprinkle a thin layer of cheese over bottom.
Pour meat mixture over cheese. Cover with another layer of chips and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees approx. 20 min. or until cheese is melted.

title: hot dog delicious
directions: Saute onion
in
oil
in
large
saucepan until tender. Stir in next
6 ingredients.
Add hot dogs to sauce and simmer 10 minutes or until heated through. Serve in warm buns.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Combine
graham cracker crumbs, 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and butter;
mix well.	Press into bottom and halfway up side of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: angel food cake with sour cream
directions: Cut cake in 1/2 horizontally.
Ice inside and out with sour cream.
Garnish with berries immediately before serving.
Sprinkle cake generously with brown sugar.

title: easy pineapple salad
directions: In a large bowl, gradually stir the undrained pineapple into the cream cheese.
Stir in the pudding mix.
Fold in pineapple chunks and whipped topping.
Cover and chill until
serving time. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: zucchini melange
directions: Place
olive
oil
in large saucepan; add cubed vegetables, salt
and
pepper to taste.
Let simmer, covered, until all vegetables	are
tender, about 30 minutes.	Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese just before serving. Serves 6.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix
sugar,
cocoa
and
salt,
gradually add cream and syrup. Cook
in
heavy
pan
(I use club aluminum) until soft ball
is reached.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, margarine and nuts. Beat
until it loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut into squares when it begins to harden.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients; melt butter and let it cool down. Add to lemon juice and eggs.
Stir into dry ingredients until well moistened.
Pour into muffin cups or lightly greased loaf pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes for muffins or 45 minutes for bread at 400°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients in cake pan (13 x 8-inch).
Mix and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Mix together
and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Add 1/2 cup shredded Swiss cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortenings and sugar.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Add flour alternately with milk, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, meal and flour together.
Combine vanilla, milk and eggs.
Add milk-egg mixture to dry mixture.
Mix together.
Bake pie shell a little before adding ingredients.
Put mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 250° until lightly brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Grease and flour desired pan.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, food coloring and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Mix well after each addition.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in, do not beat, vinegar and baking soda.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until toothpick in center come out clean.
Makes a double layer 9-inch cake or 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all together and put in a slightly oiled bundt pan. Bake about 50 minutes at 350 degrees. Good warm or cold. Freezes well. Could be more or less than 50 minutes baking time.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Bring milk, sugar and chocolate squares to full boil over medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring hard.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and beat well 1 minute.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Slice apples.
Mix with cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar and set aside.
Mix 2 cups sugar, Wesson oil, flour, eggs, baking powder, salt and vanilla in a large bowl.
(Batter will be stiff.) Beat well with spoon.
Put in Bundt pan a layer of batter, layer of apples and layer of batter.
Pour juices that are left from apple mixture on top and sides.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 4 hours.
Check halfway through cooking and add water if needed.
Serve over noodles.

title: quick dessert
directions: Place Hershey on cracker; place in microwave on paper towel. Heat until melted.
Watch carefully as cracker will burn easily. Remove from microwave and top with another cracker.
Cool.

title: paska or easter bread
directions: In large bowl, combine scalded milk, sugar, salt and butter. Cool to lukewarm.
Save 2 tablespoons of beaten eggs and add rest to mixture.
Crumble yeast in water and let stand 10 minutes.
Add to mixture.
Then add 2 cups of flour at a time until dough can be handled.
Knead on floured board for 15 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl, grease top and let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Knead again for 15 minutes.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Place in 2-quart size pans and let rise 45 minutes.
Brush with 2 tablespoons of egg that had been set aside.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: summer sausage pasta salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: fruity breakfast parfait
directions: In parfait glasses, layer pineapple, raspberries, yogurt and bananas.
Top with almonds and serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook pudding mix.
Place vanilla wafers in a large dish. Alternate sliced bananas and pudding; chill.
This is a favorite in our family.
Sometimes it doesn't have time to cool off.

title: mushroom gravy
directions: Cook sliced mushrooms in butter in a covered pan for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle in Wondra flour and stir until mixture thickens.
Lower heat; add sour cream and blend well.
Serve with turkey, pork or roast beef.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter into hot greased pan; sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Pour rest of batter over cheese.
Bake in hot oven (400°).
Just before bread browns, sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: haystack candy
directions: Mix oil and chocolate morsels together until melted.
Mix in noodles and peanuts and spoon out on wax paper.
Cool and serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Soften butter.
Add sugar and flour and mix well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Fold in coconut, chips and nuts.
Spread in a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy meat balls
directions: Combine chuck, beef, onion, beaten eggs, oatmeal, salt and pepper together.
Add enough crushed crackers to make meat easy to handle and make into balls. Dust meat balls in small amount of flour.
Brown in 1 tablespoon oil or Crisco.
After all are browned, drain off all grease and add about 1/2 to 3/4 cup catsup over the top of the balls.
Add water (enough to cover the balls halfway).
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: party chex
directions: Mix together oil, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, celery salt and chili powder.
Mix with cereals.
Bake in 200° oven for 2 hours.
Stir several times while baking.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour until until set.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients for 10 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix corn syrup, sugar and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add peanuts and cook over low heat until peanuts are brown.
Remove from heat and add baking soda. Pour into buttered 9 x 11-inch pan.
Cool.
Break apart.
(Cook approximately 5 minutes.)

title: caramel apple breakfast pudding
directions: Peel, core and slice apples (2 cups). In a small saucepan, combine apple slices and 1/4 cup water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cook, covered, over low heat until apples are tender, stirring occasionally. Drain in a colander. Transfer apples to small bowl. Gently stir cinnamon into cooked apples. Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish; add carrots and English peas.
Heat 1 stick margarine in saucepan.
Stir in 1/4 cup flour, then add 6 cups broth from chicken.
Let thicken and pour over chicken mixture.
Roll out dough and cut in strips; crisscross on top.
Cook until crust is brown on top.
Spread a little margarine on top of crust.

title: corn quiche
directions: Cut monterey jack cheese into cubes.
Combine eggs and sour creme in a large bowl.
Add corn, bread crumbs, green chillies, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in monterey jack cheese cubes. Spoon into a greased 10 inch quiche pan or a square baking pan Bake at 350 or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Bake 5 or 10 minutes longer.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Add egg last to mixture.
Put into a large pie plate and bake about 30 minutes in a moderate oven at 350°.
Cut into pie shape slices and serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Cook meat and onion together until beef is brown, about 5 minutes.
Drain
off
any
fat.
Add
remaining ingredients, except green beans; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 40 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into 9 x 9-inch ungreased square pan. Make three holes and pour oil, vinegar and vanilla in separate holes.
Pour water over all and mix with fork.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Leave in pan and frost.

title: palocenke(crepe)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put even amount of batter in a skillet with teaspoon of oil.
Fry lightly on both sides until lacy (makes 12 to 15).

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhubarb-cherry pie
directions: Mix sliced rhubarb, cherry pie filling, sugar and tapioca. Let stand 15 minutes.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Fill with rhubarb filling.
Lattice top of pie.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Soak the chicken parts in cold water, changing the water frequently.
Place the water, chicken and onions in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for another hour or so.
Serve with noodles, rice or matzo balls.

title: reuben miniatures
directions: Spread each bread slice with Russian dressing and 1 teaspoon sauerkraut.
Top with corned beef and Swiss cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves 30.

title: no fry donuts
directions: In large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour and blend for 1/2 minute on slow speed.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover.
Let rise until double or rise in refrigerator overnight.
Dough will be soft.
Roll around on flour covered board to coat with flour.
Roll gently to 1/2-inch thick and cut donuts.
Lift donuts carefully and place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with butter and let rise until double.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Coat baked donuts with cinnamon/sugar mixture.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil water; add raisins and cook uncovered 3 to 5 minutes. Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt; mix into raisins.
Return to heat; stir constantly until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat; add cinnamon and lemon juice.
Pour filling into crust.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes, until crust is golden brown.

title: pineapple-gruyere burgers
directions: Light a grill or preheat the broiler.
Grill pineapple on an oiled rack or broil until golden brown (3 minutes per side). Shape the ground chuck into four (3 1/2-inch) patties and season on both sides with salt and pepper.
Grill the burgers on an oiled grill rack or broil for 4 minutes.
Turn and cook for 3 minutes.
Place a slice of Gruyere cheese on each burger and cook until the cheese is melted, 1 minute.
Grill or toast buns.
Place burgers on buns and top each with a pineapple ring.
Mound baby lettuce. Serve with red onion and tomato slices.

title: sticky chicken and lima beans
directions: Brown chicken quarters in large saucepan.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute until chicken is almost done.
Add lima beans. Continue simmering for about 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: 7 layer chocolate cherry bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan on stovetop.
Remove once melted.
Use blender to turn graham crackers into crumbs and spread evenly over melted margarine in pan.
Spread chocolate chips over crumbs.
Spread nuts and coconut over chips.
Pour 1/2 can of condensed sweetened milk over mixture.
Spread can of cherry pie filling over all.
Then add remaining condensed milk by drizzling over cherry pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cut, when cool, into bars.

title: mother's quick chocolate cakes
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
In same pan add sugar, flour (which has been sifted with baking powder) and salt.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Do not stir until all assembled, then beat well.
Place in cupcake pans.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until done.

title: fried rice
directions: Boil water.
Add rice.	Boil 15 minutes.
Rinse in cold water and drain.	In frying pan, combine oil, soy sauce, sugar and onion.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream
cups of sugar and butter until light and fluffy for
at
least
2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs, vanilla and beat
well again.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Roll 1/2 teaspoonfuls of dough in mixture of 3 tablespoons cinnamon and 1/4
cup	of sugar;
space 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for
8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will still be soft and puffy at 400°.
Let
cool a	minute	or
two
before taking off cookie sheet.

title: easy orange coconut cake
directions: Blend the cake mix, pudding mix, Wesson oil, egg yolks, egg white and cold water together for 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until cake draws away from pan and top is springy to touch.
Mix the orange juice and sugar; let set while cake is baking.
Soak layers with the mixture.
Cover all 3 layers with Seven Minute Frosting and 1 can shredded coconut.

title: paste
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water slowly, stirring out all lumps. Cook over very low heat or in a double boiler, stirring constantly.
Remove when it begins to thicken.
Keep in covered jars.
You can thin this paste with water if necessary.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with an onion and butter.
When done, chop into chunks.
Mix together soup, sour cream and broth.
Add chicken to mixture and put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine in Baggie and spread on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: calypso pie
directions: Mix crushed Oreos with butter.	Spread into greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 gallon soft vanilla ice cream (or any flavor) on crumb mixture and freeze until firm.

title: golden graham peanut snack
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cereal and peanuts in large bowl. Heat peanut butter, margarine and cinnamon in 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally until blended.
Pour this mixture over cereal and peanuts, stirring until completely coated. Spread in ungreased rectangular baking dish.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Stir in raisins, spread mixture on a wax paper covered cookie sheet.
Let stand at least 2 hours to cool.
Then serve as a snack or place in a covered container to use the following day.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and pecans.
Roll into little balls and place on cookie sheet.
(Do not greased cookie sheet.)
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool and roll in powdered sugar again.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Mix well. Roll out thin on floured surface.
Let dry at least 10 minutes or pinch off to your liking.
Put into a pot of boiling chicken broth and 1/2 stick butter.
Boil 10 minutes.
Make a roux from 1/2 stick butter and 1/4 cup flour.
Be sure it is good and smooth before putting into broth.
You can add chicken before thickening if you wish; it isn't a must.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Pour boiling water over jello and cream cheese and stir until dissolved (use rotary beater).
Add 1 cup cold liquid.
(Use liquid from pineapple, adding water to make 1 cup.)
Stir well.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Let jell.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in milk and eggs.
Add vanilla, then mix in dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll about 1/2-inch thick.
Sugar tops or frost after cooled.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: turkey (chicken) cheese puffs
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine; beat on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Add milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in turkey and pepper.
Unroll dough and separate into 4 rectangles; press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup turkey mixture in center of each dough rectangle.
Moisten edges of each rectangle with water; bring the 4 corners to the center over filling, pinching edges to seal.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Yields 4.
Great for leftover turkey at Thanksgiving!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup margarine.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Place mixture in casserole.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup margarine and pecans.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar. Beat in eggs. Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares while slightly warm.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Add chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Boil eggs. Cut up in peas, then add mayonnaise to peas.
Chill and serve.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir in corn meal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat until smooth. (Do not overbeat.)
Pour batter into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in hot oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Place sweet potatoes in greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and orange peel in a pan.
Drain apricots and reserve syrup.
Stir 1 cup syrup into cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until boiling. Boil 2 minutes, then add apricots, butter, pecans and orange juice.
Pour over potatoes and bake uncovered for 25 minutes. Bake at 375°.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Dip nuts in egg white and then in sugar and spice mixture. Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cool and reserve 2 cups broth.
Remove chicken from bones.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Place in shallow casserole (3 quart).
Combine soup and 1 cup broth.
Pour over chicken. Mix butter and 1 cup broth.
Stir in stuffing, spoon over chicken. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pork 'n pasta bake(reduced fat)
directions: Prepare ziti and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sausage until well browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Remove saucepan from heat, stir in Ricotta, next 3 ingredients and 1/2 the sauce. Add ziti and toss gently to coat well.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over ziti mixture and sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat until well blended (use blender). Grease 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lebanon place easy ice cream
directions: Combine milk, sugar, eggs and sweetened condensed milk.
Add 2 teaspoons almond extract.
Pour into electric ice cream freezer. Add more milk, if needed, to fill freezer to mark.
Yield:
6 quarts.

title: broccoli cheez whiz rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and place in a large mixing bowl with soup and water.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and rice.
Add onions and celery with salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish and cut margarine into chunks and place over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: doggie biscuits(for your favorite canine)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, dry milk, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Mix in egg.
Add enough water so that mixture forms a ball.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put crumbs and butter on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french bread pizza
directions: Slice and butter.
Sprinkle with garlic and toast under broiler.
Spread tomato sauce and add cheese and other toppings. Broil again until cheese is brown.

title: simply sugar cookies
directions: Combine, drop mix on greased cookie sheet and cook at 350° for 10 minutes or until slightly browned.
Sprinkle tops with sugar while hot.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough onto round pizza pan and form crust.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and vanilla and spread over crust.
Garnish with fruit (kiwi, blueberries, sliced strawberries, bananas and cherries).
(Use pie mix variety on the cherries and blueberries.)

title: green onion dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Blend until almost smooth.
Cover and chill.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in large microwavable mixing bowl (4 to 6 quarts). Heat in microwave on High for about 6 minutes until butter and Velveeta are well melted.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix together Crisco, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Mix together baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves with 3/4 cup of flour.
Add the remaining 1 cup of flour. Mix with applesauce, oats and raisins. Beat until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Bake until brown.

title: apricot layer cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients; beat on low speed for 30 seconds or until moistened.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pans to a wire rack to cool completely.
Split each layer in half horizontally.
Spread the cut side of each bottom layer with 1/3 cup apricot preserves.
Replace top and set aside.

title: fudge-scotch ring
directions: In the top of a double boiler, melt chips with milk; cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Stir and mix well. Place in refrigerator and chill about 1 hour.
Drop by tablespoon to form a ring.
Decorate with nuts and cherries.

title: ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan (13x9x2).
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown - 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into rectangles about 2 x 1-1/2 inches.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain off fruit.
Cut pineapple in half.
Arrange fruit in casserole dish.
Heat in pan butter, sugar and sherry.
Cool and pour over the fruit.
cover and chill overnight in refrigerator. Before serving, heat in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover to heat, but re-cover to keep hot after baking until ready to serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in crust and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: super fried chicken
directions: Combine pancake mix and 1 package salad dressing mix; mix well and set aside.
Combine club soda, egg and 1 package salad dressing mix; stir well.
Dip chicken in club soda mixture; dredge in pancake mixture.
Allow chicken to drain 5 minutes.

title: coconut delight
directions: Crust:
Mix and press into Pyrex dish the oleo, pecans and flour. Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven or until light brown.

title: oreo cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Form into walnut size balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
(Be sure to watch, you don't want them to get too done.)
Cool.
Cream other three ingredients together.
Spread between 2 cooled cookies.

title: chocolate cupcake surprise
directions: Prepare devil's food cake mix as directed, then set aside. Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Add egg and salt; mix well.
Then stir in chocolate chips.

title: purple passion fruit salad
directions: Mix together and fold in 1 (9 or 12 ounce) container of whipped topping.

title: fresh rhubarb betty(microwave)
directions: Combine first five items in a bowl and set aside.
Put bread cubes in a bowl.
Melt butter and pour over bread.
Add vanilla and toss.
In 1 1/2-quart dish, make alternate layers of rhubarb and bread cubes, ending with buttered bread cubes.
Cook in microwave, covered, about 12 minutes or until rhubarb is cooked.
Serve warm or chilled with Cool Whip.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook according to directions on cake mix box.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onions and butter in casserole.
Cook, covered, over lowest possible heat for about 4 minutes or until potatoes are almost cooked.
Stir frequently.
If necessary, add 1 to 2 tablespoons hot water or consomme to prevent scorching.
Add rest of the hot water or bouillon.
Season with salt and pepper. Simmer, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are cooked. Sprinkle with bacon and parsley.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in medium saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Mix a small amount of lukewarm milk and sugar mixture with beaten egg.
Set egg mixture aside.
Continue to cook milk mixture until it starts to boil and thicken.
Stir in egg mixture.
Turn heat to low and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in margarine and vanilla. Pour in cooled pie crust.
When cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: ginger ale coffee
directions: Chill coffee.
Add a few grains of salt and the ice cream. Beat.
Pour into 6 tall glasses.
Fill glasses with chilled ginger ale.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill 8 hours before serving.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla in 1 1/2-quart casserole (it will be lumpy). Put margarine on top. Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Take out and stir until smooth.
Put in buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: asparagus and mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter, cooking quickly.
Remove mushrooms from pan.
Leave excess butter and juices from mushrooms in pan. Place asparagus in pan; cover.
Steam asparagus until tender, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add stir-fry sauce and mushrooms.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: creamy mocha fudge(makes about 2 pounds)
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with milk, sweetened condensed milk, instant coffee dissolved in water and vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Spread evenly into aluminum foil-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 3 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store, covered in, refrigerator.

title: quick and easy campfire chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and pour off grease.
Add beans and green chili to meat and simmer until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Will need 12 wooden skewers.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Combine butter, coconut, flour and brown sugar in a saucepan. Cook on medium heat until a rich brown color, stirring frequently. Pour into pie plate and press out to edges evenly with a fork. Allow to cool before filling.
Makes 1 (9-inch) crust (8 servings).

title: easy meal
directions: Place can opener on can.
Apply a pinch of pressure and turn handle clockwise.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
On top put 2 cups crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes until golden brown around edges.

title: "make crackerjacks"
directions: Preheat a heavy skillet.
Add shortening.
When sizzling hot, add popcorn.
As soon as it starts to pop, add salt and sugar. Shake vigorously while corn pops so melted sugar will not burn. Empty into large bowl and add a few peanuts.

title: peanut butter cream cake
directions: Mix margarine, flour and peanuts; mix well.
Press firmly into a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine peanut butter, cheese, sugar and 1 bowl Cool Whip.
Mix well with electric mixer and beat until thick.
Spread over second layer and let stand until firm.
Top with remaining bowl of Cool Whip. Grate candy bar over topping and chill.
Store in refrigerator.

title: dill dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: overnight caramel french toast
directions: Melt corn syrup, brown sugar and butter in saucepan and pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Place 6 slices bread on top of the mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Place 6 more slices of bread on top and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon together in bowl.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.
Um, Um, delicious.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Spread mayonnaise on both sides and dip in cheese crumbs until well coated.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan and shake garlic powder and parsley flakes over.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Can be eaten cold or hot.
Better for you than fried chicken.

title: chicken alyeska
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place in baking pan and pour mix over.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°, uncovered.
Baste twice.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Flour and grease a tube pan. Cream together the cream cheese, butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and vanilla flavoring. Bake 1 1/2 hours. Enjoy!

title: black beans and rice
directions: In a large skillet or saucepan, heat oil over medium-hot flame.
Add onions and saute for 5 minutes, until onion starts to soften, then add celery, carrots and garlic.
Cook until veggies start to become tender-crisp.
Add rice; stir and coat with juices in the pan.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add tomato, spices, herbs and chicken broth.
Cover, reduce heat to simmer and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add beans and continue cooking until rice is tender and beans are heated through.
Stir to keep rice from sticking.
Add Tabasco and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with crusty bread.
This can be a meal in itself or a side dish to barbecue pork or ribs.

title: cheddary chicken pot pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine soup, 1/2 cup of milk, onion, cream cheese, celery, carrots, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Cook and stir until the mixture is hot and cream cheese is melted.
Stir in the chicken and broccoli; heat through.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.

title: missouri cookies
directions: Combine the butter, milk, sugar and cocoa in saucepan; mix well.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine molasses, sugar and shortening in 4-quart saucepan; heat to boil.
Stir in baking soda.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Pour into large mixing bowl and add beaten eggs, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Beat well with mixer and gradually add sifted flour to make a workable dough.
Cover with wax paper and cool in refrigerator for one hour or more.

title: refrigerator-marinated peppers
directions: Pour solution over peppers.
Leave set out for 24 hours, then put in refrigerator.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa. Stir in melted margarine. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Then stir in milk and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans or walnuts.
Chill overnight.
Best served with Triscuits.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup and cream cheese in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until cream cheese melts. Remove from heat; stir in green beans, water chestnuts, garlic, onion, pepper and cheese.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: western meal-in-one
directions: Brown meat with garlic, onion and pepper.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Drain off fat.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish after mixing in all other ingredients, except the cheese.
Cover; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Put cheese on top; bake 15 more minutes.

title: strawberry-banana jello salad
directions: Add jello to boiling water.
Add fruit and nuts (juice and all).
Pour 1/2 into dish; let set.
Spread sour cream on top. Pour in other 1/2; let set.

title: mexican fried ice cream
directions: Scoop 4 to 5 balls of ice cream and keep frozen.
Mix corn flakes with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll balls in crumbs and freeze again.
Beat eggs and dip coated balls in remaining crumbs and freeze until ready to serve.
Heat deep hot oil to 350°.
Place ice cream on slotted spoon and lower into hot oil for 1 minute.
Place in champagne glass or dessert plate.
Drizzle with honey and top with whipped cream.
Continue to fry balls one at a time.

title: beef pie
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, 3/4 cup cornflake crumbs, barbecue sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Press meat mixture onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat margarine, lime juice, salt, pepper and garlic until smooth.
Spread liberally on both sides of fillets; marinate for 1 hour in a Pyrex baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and crushed onions.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until just done, depending on thickness of fish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour over hamburger mixture.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with chopped tomatoes and lettuce.
Serves 6 or 8 people.

title: party punch
directions: Simmer all ingredients together in a saucepan for 10 minutes. Strain and serve hot.
Makes 15 cups.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine all ingredient except nuts in a saucepan.
Boil about 3 minutes until it becomes a syrup-like consistency.
Remove from heat and add nuts immediately.
Stir until nuts are all coated and no liquid remains.
Empty onto waxed paper.
Break apart any nuts that are sticking together.
Let cool on waxed paper (you have to work fast after nuts are added to hot syrup).
After nuts have cooled, package into decorative tins and give as gifts or store for your own use.
(Makes great Christmas gifts.)

title: lite strawberry salad or mom's strawberry salad
directions: Bring the pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Stir in the Jell-O and remove from the heat.
Let mixture start to congeal and stir in the Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: mallow whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, margarine, orange juice and salt; beat until smooth.
Add 1 cup marshmallows.
Spread in 10 x 6 x 2-inch (1 1/2 quart) baking dish.
Top with remaining marshmallows.
Melt remaining margarine.
Combine with cereal and sugar.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cook sliced onion and celery with leaves in butter until cooked, then add chicken broth and cauliflower.
Heat to the boiling point.
Add light cream.
Do not let soup boil after adding the cream.
Season to taste.

title: rice pilau
directions: Cook green pepper, onions, oil and mushrooms until tender. Add water, tomatoes and parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice last; cook until rice is tender.

title: tuna and red pepper salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine vinegar and next 4 ingredients; drizzle over tuna mixture.
Toss gently. Cover and chill
up to 1 1/2 hours, if desired.
Arrange on radicchio and leaf lettuce; serve immediately.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add vanilla, vinegar and oil.
Pour 2 cups water over all.
Mix until all lumps are gone. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in an 8 or 9-inch skillet. Mix the 5 dry ingredients together.
Beat the egg and add to the dry ingredients.
Add milk; stir to mix.
Pour in heated skillet. Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes, or until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 325°.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onions, covered, in butter for about 20 minutes, or until tender.
Add condensed beef broth, Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; bring to boiling.
Sprinkle toasted bread with cheese; place under broiler until cheese is lightly browned.
Ladle soup into bowls and float bread atop.
(Or, place a bread slice on soup in each broiler-proof soup bowl; sprinkle with cheese.
Broil until cheese is lightly browned.)
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
