directions: Mix the first five ingredients, then add flour and baking powder.
Chill for 10 minutes, covered.
Bake at 400° until the edges turn.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Mix other ingredients and add gradually.
Roll thin and cut into desired shape.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Use round pizza pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, cool, debone and cut chicken into cubes.
Mix bread cubes, margarine and water and pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together chicken, green onions, celery, mayonnaise and salt. Spread on top of stuffing.
Beat 2 eggs; add milk.
Mix well and pour over chicken. Let stand overnight in refrigerator before putting in oven.
Spread can of soup over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
During last 10 minutes, sprinkle 1 cup of shredded cheese over top.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: amazing angel pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender.
Blend at low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Pound into both sides of meat.
Cut beef into thin strips.
Place butter in 2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave oven on Full power for 30 seconds or until melted.
Add meat.
Cook in microwave oven on Full power for 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Stir in onion and garlic.
Cook on Full power for 2 to 3 minutes, or until onion and garlic are tender.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, water and tomato paste.
Cook on Full power for 8 to 10 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat on Full power for 1 minute.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 4.

title: i don't know, but it's good
directions: Brown both meats with 1/4 of a stick of butter.
Drain, then add chopped cabbage and 1/4 stick of butter and water as needed to the ground meats.
Cook until the cabbage is wilted, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Boil the spuds, drain and mash.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa in a large bowl.
(Do not use mixer.)
Add coffee and salad dressing.
Pour mixture in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Test for doneness.
Frost with Glossy Chocolate Frosting (recipe in cookbook).

title: yuletide pudding (granny's legacy)
directions: Place broken gingersnaps in a large bowl.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Add to gingersnaps.

title: broiled flank steak
directions: Remove fat and covering membrane from flank steak.
Tenderize with fork.
Mix ingredients.
Lay flank steak in a broiling pan and spread on half of the marinade.
Turn and spread with rest of marinade.
Cover with wax paper and leave for at least 30 minutes (overnight is best).
Broil.
Best if served rare to medium.
Cut across the grain in very thin slices.

title: penoche
directions: Mix sugars and milk well.
Bring to the boiling point, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to 236° or until a small amount when dropped into cold water will form a soft ball.
Add butter and cool until lukewarm, then beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts and pour into greased pan.
When cold, cut into squares.
If mixture should curdle, it will be smooth after beating.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Heat juice.
Add to Jell-O.
Add cream cheese while mixture is still hot.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Let congeal and serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise, if desired.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook beef, onion and peppers in large skillet until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives, garlic, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder and pepper. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until thick.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 6 ounces of Cheddar cheese.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, milk, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add ground meat and cooked rice; mix thoroughly.
Remove center vein of cabbage leaves, keeping each leaf in one piece.
Immerse leaves in boiling water until limp, about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Place 1/4 to 1/2 cup meat mixture on each leaf.
Fold in sides.
Starting at unfolded edge, roll up each leaf, making sure folded sides are included in roll.

title: cranberry bread
directions: You will also need vegetable oil spray.
Do not use vegetable oil spray near an open flame or a heat source.
Read and follow directions on can before using.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour and sugar.
Add onions, then milk and egg. Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat at 375°.
When done, they will float.
Put on brown paper to drain.
Yields about 24 hush puppies.

title: rice krispies crunch
directions: In medium saucepan over low heat, melt almond bark, stirring constantly.
Stir in peanut butter; remove from heat and cool slightly.
Stir in cereal, marshmallows and peanuts; mix well. Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls onto wax paper covered cookie sheets.
Refrigerate to set.

title: spicy stir-fry
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute garlic and vegetables in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients; cook, covered for 10 minutes or until done.
Serve over white rice.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles, if desired.

title: deep freeze biscuits
directions: Stir together dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to buttermilk.
Add milk to dry mixture and mix well.
Roll out about 1/2-inch thick and cut in desired size.
Freeze on cookie sheets.
When frozen, place in plastic bags.
Close securely and store in freezer.
About 30 minutes before baking, dip in melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Take out desired amount to serve.

title: imperial crabs
directions: Simmer vegetables in butter.
Put crabmeat in bowl.
Add simmered vegetables and all other ingredients.
Mix gently and fill cleaned crab shells.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: baked fish
directions: Take fish fillet and salt and pepper to taste.
Dip in batter, then in potato flakes.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, butter and Italian seasoning.
Make a ball and roll in nuts.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook ground beef until brown, then drain. Put all ingredients in pot. Cook until all ingredients are done. Great for crock-pot.

title: fried okra(louisiana)
directions: Wash okra; trim ends.
Slice into bite-size pieces; set aside. In a medium bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, salt, red pepper and black pepper; mix well.
In a shallow bowl, beat together egg and milk.
Dip okra into milk mixture; coat well.
Fry about one-third of the okra at a time in deep, hot fat for 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Drain on paper towel.

title: hobo burgers
directions: Form ground beef into 4 patties and place each on a large sheet of aluminum foil.
Bring sides of foil up so that it will hold other ingredients.
Peel carrots, potatoes and onion.
Slice thin. Place one slice of cheese on top of each hamburger patty.
Then put other vegetables on top of this.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put 1/2 slice of cheese on top of each and bring foil up and seal to form a tent type container.
Place on cookie sheet and cook at 400° for approximately 1 hour.
Makes a complete meal for 4.

title: bob evans salad dressing
directions: Add together in blender until mixed the sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and onion.
Add the oil, lemon juice and celery seed. Beat until well mixed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients. Dot with margarine and bake at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold and let set for several hours.

title: frozen strawberry cream cake
directions: Prepare and mix all ingredients well.
Spray a tube pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan.
Cover with plastic wrap or foil. Place in freezer overnight.
Turn out of pan and slice as desired. Serve with whipped cream or as desired.

title: coffee punch(serves 50)
directions: Combine coffee, sugar and hot water.
Let cool and add milk, vanilla and chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add ice cream 30 minutes before serving.

title: italian beef
directions: Rub roast with garlic; sprinkle with spices.
Brown in 1/4 pound butter.
Add onion, celery, tomato paste, wine and water. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Drain and strain juices.
Cool.
When roast is cold, slice very thin.
Arrange slices in pan and cover with strained drippings.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve warm on buns.

title: butter icing
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar.
Stir in cream and vanilla.
Add additional cream if icing appears too thick.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until fork tender.
Peel, then shred into large bowl.
Stir in sour cream, chopped onions, 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn into greased 2 quart casserole; top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until heated through.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: roast in a bag
directions: Before bedtime, set oven at 175° to 200°.
Put meat, water and onions into seasoning bag.
Next morning, turn oven off.
Boil potatoes and carrots until almost done.
Add salt and pepper.
Put meat and all its juice into electric skillet.
Add potatoes and carrots; simmer until they are cooked.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch or flour and water.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes. Meat can be frozen.
Bags found in grocery in seasonings.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix and set aside flour and sugar. In a pot boil margarine, cocoa and coke; pour over sugar and flour mixture. Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla, and marshmallows. Mix and pour into greased oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Leave cake in pan. Mix icing and pour over cake.

title: minute steak and creole gravy
directions: Dredge steak in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Brown coated steak in bacon grease (shortening may be used).
Remove browned steak to plate.
In pan drippings, saute onions until brown.
Add tomatoes and water.
Chop tomatoes as they begin to heat.
Add steak back to gravy and simmer until steak is tender.
Serve with hot biscuits! Delicious!

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine nuts with 1 teaspoon flour.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and powder.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and oil, mixing well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Stir in zucchini.
Stir in prepared nuts.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and
flour
by
hand. Add sour cream.
Grease small muffin tins.
Drop
teaspoons into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until barely golden brown.
Makes 48 tiny biscuits.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Bake in tube pan for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Cut fruit; add nuts and 1/2 cup flour (not included above) in mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar together. Add eggs, vanilla, brandy flavoring and soda mixed in hot water or whiskey.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Then add fruit and mix together.

title: applesauce spice loaf(low sodium - low-fat - low cholesterol)
directions: Grease and lightly flour 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.

title: pudding pops(kids)
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Pour into six 5 ounce paper cups.
Insert wooden sticks or plastic spoon into each for a handle.
Press a square of aluminum foil or wax paper down onto pudding to cover, piercing center of foil square with handle.
Freeze until firm.
Press firmly on bottom of cup to release pop.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Peel and cut up apples and cook.
Mix in sugar.
Add soda, cinnamon, Crisco and margarine.
Let cool.

title: tv snack
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Melt margarine.
Pour over and mix well.
Spread on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°, stirring often for 20 minutes.

title: rice dish
directions: Melt butter; add onion soup mix and rice.
Stir well.
Add 3 cups of hot water.
Stir well.
Bake in casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix ingredients and press in bottom of 8-inch square pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: apple-cherry brown betty
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Combine low-fat yogurt, oil and orange juice; stir well.
Add yogurt mixture to flour mixture and stir just until blended. Spoon into a 9-inch square baking dish coated with cooking spray; set aside.
Combine apple slices and lemon juice; toss gently. Arrange apples and cherries over batter in pan; sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.

title: sesame chicken appetizers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl. Stir well.
Cut each chicken breast half into 4 strips.
Add chicken to marinade. Cover and chill 1 hour. Remove chicken from marinade.
Weave 1 chicken strip on each of 16 skewers.
Coat with sesame seed. Place on rack in a broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5-inches from heat for 3 minutes, then turn skewers. Broil 3 minutes or until done. Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: In a small bowl, mix together 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and chocolate chips.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream together butter, 1 cup of sugar and eggs, then beat until light.
Add sour cream, vanilla, water, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and lemon rind.
Gradually stir into milk. Add egg yolk; blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Pile lightly on pie filling.
Bake at 325° until golden.

title: spiced apple turkey
directions: Clean and pat dry entire inside and outside of bird; season outside and cavity with salt, pepper and rosemary.
Place in a large roasting pan, surrounded with chopped celery, parsnips, turnips, carrots and onion.
Add chicken stock to pan; cover and roast at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Before carving, prepare gravy from pan juices.
Serve with Spiced Apples.

title: grandma's microwave fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in large bowl.
Remove from microwave; add sugar and milk until creamy and smooth.
Place in microwave on high; stir after 30 seconds.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown chopped beef in 1 tablespoon oil.
When brown, add seasons which have been mixed together.
Add beans and let cook until time to eat.

title: granny cake(from my granny kirk)
directions: Mix together everything except brown sugar and coconut.
Pour into a greased baking pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Mix sugar and coconut together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana flip
directions: Mix 7 tablespoons butter and graham cracker crumbs; put in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: no-fuss lasagna
directions: Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Arrange a layer of uncooked noodles on sauce.
Top with 1 cup sauce, 1/2 of all cheeses, then another cup of sauce.
Repeat until noodles run out.
Top with rest of sauce (cover all noodles) and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bingo bars
directions: Beat eggs and gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add salad oil and blend in.
Sift all dry ingredients. Combine (3) baby foods in bowl, alternating dry ingredients and baby food to egg and sugar mix.
Pour in greased and floured jelly roll size pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While bars are cooling, prepare icing.

title: chinese pineapple steamed sponge cake
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/4 cup syrup.
Pat slices dry with paper towel.
Line bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan with wax paper. Arrange pineapple on bottom.
Beat egg yolks with syrup, sugar and vanilla on high speed of electric mixer, about 5 minutes until light and fluffy.
Slowly mix in flour, cornstarch and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold 1/2 the egg whites into batter with wire whisk.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Fold in remaining egg whites until thoroughly blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Tap pan to remove air bubbles.
Cover with foil, forming dome to allow cake to rise.
Bring water to a boil in wok.
Set cake on steamer rack.
Cover and steam 35 minutes or until done.
Turn upside-down and cool.
Remove waxed paper.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Cover with slices of rye bread.
Butter outsides of bread. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 4 to 6 minutes per side (check frequently).
Serve with pickles and chips.

title: mexican seven layered dip
directions: Layer all ingredients, except taco seasoning, as written.
Add taco seasoning to taste.
Serve with corn chips.

title: special cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in bowl.
Add drained pineapple and dates. Mix.
Form into a ball and roll in nuts.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.
(Ritz are the best!)

title: italian pot roast
directions: Place roast in crockpot; combine remaining ingredients. Pour over roast and cook on high for 5 hours, or on high for 1 hour and on low for 7 hours.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and green chilies in butter. Add soup and broth; blend. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. While sauce simmers, soften tortillas by dipping each in simmering mixture a few seconds. Place a small amount of chicken on each tortilla and roll up tightly.
Place in lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish. Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
May be frozen. Makes 12 enchiladas.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Blend together for 2 minutes, pour into greased pie pan. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar or sugar substitute on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: ms. owens' potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
Mix well with cheese, soup, onion and sour cream.
Put in greased casserole.
Melt stick of butter and pour over top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can add mushrooms, meat, celery seed, parsley and pepper for variety.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Boil noodles for 8 to 10 minutes.
Brown beef and drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, make 2 layers of sauce, noodles, Parmesan cheese, beef, Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
The top layer can be made of sauce, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Blend together.
Press into 8 x 8-inch pan (ungreased).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruity juice fizz
directions: Cut the oranges or lemons into slices and put them on a plate. Pour all of the juices and the seltzer or club soda into a pitcher.
Chill the Fruity Juice Fizz in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.
Pour into glasses.
Put 1 orange or lemon slice on edge of each glass.
Serve.
Makes 10 glasses.

title: pasa de shuta(dish to pass)
directions: Brown pork and beef; drain fat.
Chop vegetables and saute until tender.
Stir in tomato soup, mushroom soup and tomato sauce.
Add cinnamon, cloves, salt and chili powder.
Cook spaghetti.
Drain and add to mix.
Stir well.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook roast until brown on all sides.
Remove, pour off fat and set aside.
In Dutch oven, combine mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling, then return roast to pan.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook for 2 hours, turning roast occasionally. Add potatoes and carrots.
Cover; cook 40 minutes more, or until roast and vegetables are fork-tender.
Transfer roast and vegetables to plate; slice and cover to keep warm.
In cup, stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup of water until smooth. Gradually add to sauce in Dutch oven.
Over medium heat, cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve sauce with or over roast.

title: the easiest aspic in the world
directions: Take lemon jello and heat V-8 juice until the jello dissolves. Add vinegar if you want to.
If you would like to impress your family or friends, you can add olives or celery and put it in a mold.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, oleo and nuts together. Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Reserve 1 cup baked for topping. Let cool.

title: western hash
directions: Brown the chuck.
Add all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: potato onion bake
directions: Layer a third of the potatoes and onions in a greased casserole dish.
In a saucepan, combine butter, cheese soup, flour and milk; stirring constantly, cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat, and stir in grated cheese and salt.
Pour a third of the sauce over the potatoes and onions.
Repeat these layers two more times.
Cover with foil and cook on 350 degrees for 1 hour or until potatoes and onions are tender.

title: gig's fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Add fruit and graham crackers.
Use immediately or will keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: peas and rice(low-fat)
directions: Saute onion until tender in nonstick pan. Cook rice in chicken broth and onion until done. Add peas, salt and pepper and mix well.
Put in serving dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.

title: sausage and potatoes
directions: Cut sausage in half. Poke holes in sausage. Peel potatoes and quarter. Put in aluminum pan, 1 side sausage and 1 side potatoes. Cut onions. Put on top. Sprinkle olive oil on potatoes, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: walking salad
directions: Mix well, then sprinkle with sugar; let stand.
Take the core of apples out, fill with salad and put apple back on with toothpick.
Place in cool place until used.
Good to serve while cooking outdoors.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Drain.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serving size:

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Mix 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon. Roll quartered biscuits in sugar/cinnamon
and place in buttered Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nuts on top.
Bring butter and 3/4 cup sugar to boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and turn out of pan.

title: pina colada muffins
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Add other ingredients.
Mix 1 minute.
Do not overmix.
Grease tins or line with paper cups. Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel delight
directions: Melt margarine and caramels in microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in condensed milk.
Dip marshmallow into mixture. Roll in Rice Krispies; put in 1 3/4-inch bake cup.

title: ann's special banana pudding
directions: Blend sugar, flour and milk. Cook until thick (stirring constantly). Beat eggs. Combine with custard. Cook until thick. Line glass dish with wafers, sliced bananas and custard. Repeat with several layers. Top with whipped cream.

title: spicy beef and vegetables
directions: Cut beef across the grain into thin strips.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat; add onions, pepper, mushrooms, garlic and salt and cook, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes until vegetables are tender.
With a slotted spoon, remove vegetables to bowl.
Add remaining tablespoon oil to skillet; add beef and cook over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, about 3 minutes, until browned.
Add peanut butter, 1/2 cup water, soy sauce, crushed red pepper flakes and vegetables.
Stir until mixture is blended and heated through. Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all ingredients except bread.

Refrigerate overnight. Scoop out center of pumpernickel bread and fill cavity with dip. Use center of bread you removed, torn into bite-size pieces, and all types of raw vegetables, potato chips or crackers as dippers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos (a potato masher works well).
Combine already mixed pudding with Cool Whip.
Layer Oreos with mixture of pudding and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate or serve when made.

title: sour cream shrimp
directions: Saute onions, mushroom and shrimp in butter.
Add salt, flour and sour cream.
Heat until hot.
Serve over rice.	Time of preparation: 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: quick and easy taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until warm.
Serve with corn bread.

title: no bake peanut butter balls
directions: Stir all ingredients together until well blended.
Roll in balls and sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: oriental basting sauce
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
(I marinate approximately 2 pounds boneless, skinless chicken in this mixture.)
Grill marinated chicken using sauce to baste while grilling.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Heat a small amount of oil in a large skillet.
Fry chicken until browned.
Drain.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, saute onions in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix together. Add bananas and lemon juice.
Mix all together.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix.
Add pecans and stir well. Grease bread pan.
Heat oven to 325° and bake 1 hour.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix the hamburger, bread crumbs, onion soup and eggs as for meat loaf.
Add salt to taste.
Add more bread crumbs, if needed. Make into patties, dip in flour and brown on each side.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran Flakes and let soak.
In a separate bowl, cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add buttermilk and "water-bran" mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat well.
"Fold in" All-Bran.
Put in tightly covered container and store in fridge.
Keeps as long as 6 weeks.

title: vegetarian four bean chili
directions: Heat oil in a large pot over medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; saute 4 minutes until onion is softened.
Add carrot; cook, covered, for 2 minutes.
Add zucchini, summer squash, chili powder, oregano and cumin; saute for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes (carefully breaking up with a wooden spoon), beer and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer, partially covered, for 15 minutes.
Stir in all beans.
Simmer, stirring frequently, for 10 minutes to heat through.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together. Add eggs; mix well. Sift dry ingredients together, then add to egg mixture. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Dough will be stiff. Form into balls and flatten with a fork, making a crisscross pattern. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: janet's sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, turning once.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil fryer in salted water until tender.
Bone and cut into bite-size.
Cook in 1 cup chicken broth the celery, onion and pepper.
Then add soup, mushrooms, pimento and cheese.
Add to cooked and drained spaghetti and chicken.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions.
Melt butter in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Slowly cook onions in butter until lightly browned.
Add bouillon cubes, water and onions.
Cover; add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to soup.
Stir.
Shred cheese.
To serve soup, place a thin slice of French bread in the bottom of each individual ovenware serving bowl.
Ladle soup into bowls.
Top with layer of shredded cheese. Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Knead on lightly floured board.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: low-fat turkey stew
directions: Cook fresh ground turkey in skillet until brown.
Cook the frozen vegetables according to directions in the microwave.
Add the vegetables to ground turkey and mix well together.
Add juice and cook until thick as desired.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream well margarine and sugar.
Add sugar and flour; mix well.
Add egg yolks, lemon juice and rind.
Beat well.
Slowly add milk while beating.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake 12 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Add vanilla. Alternate eggs and flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: confetti jello cake
directions: Prepare jello the day before in 3 different pans; when molded, cut in small cubes.
Mix jello cubes.
Beat heavy cream and sugar and whip.
Melt Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup warm water and add pineapple juice.
Mix gelatine with heavy cream by hand.
Line bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan with Lady Fingers and fill with gelatin and heavy cream mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in open roaster at 450° for 30 minutes.
Combine and thoroughly mix remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over ribs. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: watergate icing
directions: Beat together until consistency for pudding.

title: coffee breakfast drink
directions: Place oats in blender container.
Blend about 1 minute, stopping blender occasionally to stir oats.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend on high speed about 1 minute or until smooth.

title: orange sweet potatoes(diabetic)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Remove skins.
Mash pulp, add remaining ingredients and whip until fluffy.
Place in a one-quart ungreased casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 6.
Calories per serving: 95.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and enough powdered sugar to create a crumbly texture.
Prepare pudding according to package directions. Reserve 1 tablespoon peanut butter mixture.
Add larger portion of peanut butter mixture to pie crust shell.
Pour pudding over mixture.
Spread desired amount of whipped topping to top. Sprinkle with remaining peanut butter mixture over pie.
Arrange peanut butter cups on top of pie.
Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: festive chicken log(8 x 2-inches)
directions: Cut raw chicken breast in pieces.
Dip in yogurt, mixed with crushed garlic.
Dip in wheat germ, mixed with 1 teaspoon poultry seasoning.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Put in picks and serve warm with dashes of soy sauce and honey mustard dressing for dipping.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, saute onion in margarine for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat; stir in flour and blend well.
Stir in chicken broth, garlic and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low.
Add broccoli and milk.
Simmer 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Stir in half and half and cheese and cook, stirring until cheese melts.
Yummy.

title: squash pickles
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and spices to a boil.
Add squash, onions and bell peppers.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add pimento peppers, chopped.
Stir well.
Pack while hot into jars.
Seal.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and both sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 cup candies.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased baking sheet.
Decorate tops with remaining candy.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate praline layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a small heavy saucepan, combine butter, brown sugar and whipping cream. Cook over low heat just until butter is melted, stirring occasionally. Pour into two 9 or 8 inch round cake pans and sprinkle evenly with chopped pecans. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, oil, water and eggs. Beat two minutes at high speed. Carefully spoon batter over pecan mixture. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center. Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely.

In a small bowl, beat whipping cream until soft peaks form. Blend in powdered sugar and vanilla; beat until stiff peaks form. To assemble cake, place 1 layer on serving plate, praline side up. Spread with half of the whipped cream. Top with second layer, praline side up; spread top with remaining whipped cream. Garnish with whole pecans and chocolate curls. Store in refrigerator.

title: snickers pie
directions: Soften ice cream and combine with pudding mix; blend well. Stir in peanut butter until well mixed.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into a 9 inch pie pan coated with nonstick cooking spray and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving.
Slice and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon chiffon cake
directions: Mix pie filling as directed on box.
Cut down sugar amount to 2/3 cup.
Break up half of sponge cake.
Put into a large spring-form tin (greased).
Pour 1/2 of pie filling mixture over cake in pan.
Repeat and put in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Decorate with strawberries or coconut if desired.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Combine pickle slices, vinegar and sugar.
Tie spices in small piece of cheesecloth and let mixture stand at room temperature stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves (about 4 hours).
Return half the pickles to the jar.
Add spice bag, remaining pickles, then fill jar with the syrup.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Brown meat.
Add all ingredients and cook 15 minutes.
Spoon on buns.

title: grits casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, bring the water to a boil.
Add the salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in the grits.
Lower the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from the heat and stir in the butter and 1 cup cheese.

title: broccoli with rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, saute onion and celery in margarine until clear.
Cook broccoli until tender. Drain well.
Add to onion and celery, stir in rice and Tabasco. Add soup and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake for about 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until ready to pour.

title: crawfish stuffed squash
directions: Boil squash in unsalted water until tender.
Drain and mash well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Saute onions & celery in butter until soft.
Add milk, crawfish and breadcrumbs and mix well. Season with salt & pepper and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with breadcrumbs and bake at 350 degrees until brown.
Serves 6.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add jam to egg yolks.
Mix together. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Bake in 3 layer greased and floured cake pans in 350° oven. Use boiled frosting for filling and on top of cake.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix biscuit mix and water.
Roll out.
Spread sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Roll like pinwheel cookies. Slice and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked sausage and egg breakfast
directions: Fry sausage until light brown.
Drain all grease.
Place 6 slices of bread in 2 quart baking dish.
Spread 1/2 cheese and sausage over bread.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour 1/2 mixture on top.
Add 6 slices of bread and remainder of sausage and cheese and pour remainder of eggs and milk over top.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour.

title: claudine's carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Form a well in center and stir in oil, eggs, carrots and nuts until mixed well.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix ingredients on medium until mixed.	Pour into crust and freeze.
Remove from freezer 5 minutes before serving.
May use fat-free ingredients and is just as tasty.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prick top of warm brownies at 1-inch intervals using a fork.
Drizzle with liqueur.
Let cool and crumble.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all together the sugar, oil and molasses.
Add eggs and flour with soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Mix all together and add boiling water.
This makes a thin batter, but it is okay.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes.
Add nuts to this if you care for them and can afford them.

title: hamburger vegetable medley
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart glass casserole.
Stir in carrots, celery and green pepper.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Re-cover.
Microwave on reheat for 14 to 16 minutes or until hot.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: raspberry jello dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: prescription
directions: Making Colby cheese involves adding cool water to the curds after cooking.
This results in a moist, mild porous cheese. Colby does not store well.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with 1 can French fried onions.
Bake in oven 15 or 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on bottom of buttered casserole dish, add squash mixture, cover with more bread crumbs and add butter slices.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sugar oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls. Roll the balls in sugar. Mash the balls flat and place on nonstick cooking pan. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour tuna, pork or chicken
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and combine it with vinegar and sugar.
Mix soy sauce with flour and then add to pineapple mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Add onions, green pepper, pineapple and tomatoes.
Simmer for four minutes.
Add tuna, broken into large flakes, and cook just long enough to heat.
Serve with chow mein noodles if desired.

title: mushroom rice stuffing
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add onion, celery and parsley. Cook over low heat until tender, stirring constantly.
Add cooked rice, mushrooms and seasonings.
Toss together lightly.
Makes enough stuffing for a 12 to 15 pound turkey.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and milk.
Add chopped pepper and onion.
Cut beef into small pieces and add to mixture along with salt and pepper. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown stew beef with ham seasoning. Add celery and onions. When meat is cooked completely, put in crock-pot. Add all other ingredients and simmer on low several hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer half the cabbage, bell pepper and onion.
Then add next half the same.
Pour can of sauce over this. Put grated Mozzarella cheese to cover top.
Bake at 400°, covered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grits souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish or souffle dish.
Scald milk, add grits.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add salt, baking powder, butter and sugar.
Mix well. Beat egg yolks.
Add to grits.
Beat whites to soft peak; fold in.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and seasoning salt. Roll into a ball.
Roll in pecans and refrigerate.

title: rosemary lemonade for 6
directions: Mix rosemary, 1 cup water and sugar in a pan and boil gently for 5 minutes.
Strain out rosemary and add 3 cups water, lemon juice and salt.
Stir well.
Serve well iced.
Delicious!

title: peanut butter and jelly french toast
directions: Spread peanut butter on 6 slices of bread. Spread jelly on the other 6 slices of bread.
Put one slice of each together to form sandwiches.
In mixing bowl, lightly beat eggs. Add milk and salt. Mix together.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Dip sandwiches in egg mixture, coating well.
Place in skillet. Brown both sides. Serve immediately. Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese crunchers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine over hot (not boiling) water the butterscotch chips and margarine.
Stir in graham crackers and nuts when chips are melted and smooth.
Stir with a fork until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Reserve 2 cups of mixture for the topping.
Press remaining crumbs into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: munch kins
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients with wire whisk.
Fold in crackers and mix well.
Put in airtight container.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash peas.
Place in soup pot.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Thin with milk or water to desired consistency.

title: buttercrunch
directions: Combine
in a large saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until
it
cracks
hard when tested in cold water.	Remove from heat while testing.
Add 1 cup chocolate bits and quickly turn candy
into
generously
buttered
pan.
Spread
in
thin sheet. When cold, break into large pieces.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In 9 x 12-inch dish, put in layers the first 7 ingredients as shown.
Then spread mayonnaise over all to seal.
Seal bowl and refrigerate.
Toss just before serving.

title: flavored milks
directions: For each serving, fill glass with milk and add one of the ingredients.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Combine vegetables and cheese; spread in greased deep dish pie plate.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 375° or until golden brown or inserted knife comes out clean.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's great peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add both sugars and continue creaming until well mixed.
Slightly beat eggs and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Sift flour with baking soda and add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets and bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 75 cookies.

title: finger paint
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water; set aside.

Combine laundry starch with remaining cold water in medium saucepan; add the hot water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with wooden spoon until mixture comes to a full boil and has become completely thickened.
Remove from heat; blend in the softened gelatin. Add soap and stir until completely dissolved.
Add food coloring or paint to all or part of the mixture until desired color is obtained, adding no more than 1 tablespoon coloring or paint to each recipe.
Store in covered containers.
Recipe may be multiplied.

title: great waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fix on hot waffle iron.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter.
Press into bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch) or dish.
Beat powdered sugar, vanilla and 1 stick butter together for 10 minutes (important step).
Add eggs and continue to beat.
Spread over crumb layer.
Peel bananas and cut in half lengthwise and layer over cream mixture.
Drain pineapple and spoon on top of bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts. Chill 4 hours.
If desired, garnish each serving with cherry.
Cut into squares.
Makes 20 or more.

title: any meat casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Combine soup, milk, green pepper, onion and pepper and place over low heat.
Add cheese, stirring occasionally until the cheese is melted.
(You may use cream of cheese soup without thinning instead of cheese.)
Mix macaroni with cheese mixture.
Pour 1/2 of it in casserole and top with meat.
Add remaining sauce and macaroni.
Bake in 350° oven 15 or 20 minutes until sauce is bubbling.

title: bottomless chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°. In a large bowl, combine the soup, milk, chicken and peas and carrots; mix well. Pour the filling mixture into a 9-inch deep-dish pie plate. Cover with the pie crust, pressing against the pie plate to seal and flute, if desired. Make several slits in the crust to create steam vents. Place pie on a rimmed baking sheet and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through and the crust is golden. Let sit for 5 minutes, then cut into wedges and serve.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Put 3/4 cup of coconut and 3/4 cup of pecans in bottom of 9-inch pie crust.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and flour well, then add liquid ingredients.
Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) deep dish or 3 regular pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: red cabbage casserole
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt shortening.
Add cabbage, onion, lemon juice, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Stir well.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes (until cabbage is crisp-tender).
Add apples and cook 10 to 15 minutes more, until cabbage and apples are tender.
Stir in jelly and put in serving dish.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add 1 cup quick grits and cook for 10 minutes with a rolling boil.
Add cheese, tabasco and garlic powder.
In a bowl, beat an egg with a fork.
Blend 1/2 cup of the cheese grits with egg and add to the hot mixture.
Stir thoroughly. Pour into rectangular Pyrex dish.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until top is lightly browned.
Let set until cool.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread thin layer.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Chop onion and green pepper coarsely.
Cook in butter until limp.
Stir in flour as smoothly as possible.
Add milk. Gradually season with salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles.
Stir in tuna.
Pour into a shallow baking dish.

title: aunt sta's simple candy(great to make with little children!)
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips carefully (in the top of a double boiler).
When melted, remove from heat; add nuts and chow mein noodles.
Stir, then drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet lined with waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: date-nut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven. Cut into squares while warm.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Use an 8-inch square or round pan.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Drop onto cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: kraut salad
directions: Chop all vegetables fine.
Mix sugar and vinegar.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
I prefer the Bavarian style sauerkraut but any kind will do.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese should be at room temperature. Mix all ingredients together. Roll in pecans and/or potato chips.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add nuts and eggs (beaten).
Add dry ingredients, apples and nuts.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.
May be served hot or cold.
It's good with an icing of 2 cups powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon butter and enough hot coffee to mix.
Will be thin.
Spread on cake.

title: bacon wrapped asparagus bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly coat asparagus spears with olive oil and season with black pepper. Gather 3 - 4 asparagus spears together and wrap with a slice of bacon. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Place bundles of asparagus spears on a slotted broiler pan. Bake for 12 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix creamed butter with sugar, egg yolks, flour or cornstarch and pineapple.
Beat egg whites stiff and add last.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: braised sirloin tips
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of the butter in skillet.
Add fresh mushrooms and cook until they just begin to turn brown.
Put into deep casserole.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter and oil into skillet and heat.
Brown meat on all sides.
Remove to the casserole where the mushrooms are waiting.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Beat egg; add sugar, shortening and milk and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Lastly stir in raspberries.
Bake at 375°.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Layer with a row of potatoes, dry ingredients and then cheese mixture.
Repeat layers, then pour boiling water over all layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ground meat, Spanish rice and Ranch Style beans together and place in casserole dish.
Add just enough water to nacho cheese soup to spread on top of casserole.
Take small can Durkee fried onions and sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake until onions brown and casserole bubbles, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8 jumbo muffin cups with nonstick vegetable spray.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda and ginger.
In a large bowl, with wire whisk or fork, mix carrots, yogurt, egg substitute, applesauce, raisins, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
With spoon, stir flour mixture into carrot mix until all is moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake for 30 minutes or until pick inserted into center of each comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Each muffin contains 280 calories, 0 grams fat, 1 milligram cholesterol and 220 milligrams sodium.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: washington's cherry nut bread
directions: Beat vigorously all but cherries and nuts for 1/2 minute. Stir in cherries and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter until tender.
Add milk, soup, corn and seasonings.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until chowder is hot, but not boiling.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix rhubarb with 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Add last.
Cream together the remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar, shortening, eggs and flour.
Then add the baking soda, cinnamon, vanilla and sour milk. Add the rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle 10x sugar on top when done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add diced apples and mix.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and beat, then add nuts or raisins.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 90 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Very good!

title: hobo potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Place in baking dish.
Add onion, Greek seasoning, salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Slice butter; put over potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.
May be cooked on grill, takes about 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook the rhubarb, sugar and Jell-O over low heat (no water). Stir often. Cool until partly set.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip. Add nuts.
Chill for several hours.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Let set on cookie sheet for 5 minutes before removing.

title: secret chocolate sensation
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, lard and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Blend in 1 cup very hot water.
Pour into greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: 9-layer mexican dip
directions: Layer in order as listed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with chips.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cinnamon and salt. Stir pumpkin, eggs, dark corn syrup and vanilla with the first three. Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve with spicy cream and decorate.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Mix bread crumbs, garlic powder, Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper.
Cover chicken with bread crumb mix and brown both sides in small amount of oil.
Remove chicken; set aside.
In pan combine 1/2 stick butter and 1 chopped garlic clove; brown.
Throw in sliced mushrooms.
Saute about 15 minutes.
Pour in chicken mixture and wine (to cover).
Simmer 40 minutes to 1 hour, depending on amount of chicken used.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Stir by hand.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Swirl batter and add remaining batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: superb ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cover.
Chill for 1 hour.
Remove and add nuts, if desired.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Finely mince salmon.
Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup cold stock.
Add 1 cup boiling stock; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
As gelatin thickens, add the mayonnaise.
Beat until frothy.
Add salmon and seasonings.
Fold in cream.
Pour into fish mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve on shredded lettuce with cucumber sauce.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O, water, Mountain Dew and pineapple.
Let set.
Spread lemon pie filling on top.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pie filling.
Refrigerate.
Works best in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Put roast into crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and soup mix.
Do not add water.
Cover and set crock-pot on high for 1 hour, turn to low and cook 6 to 8 hours.
This gravy is real good with rice or creamed potatoes.

title: sausage delights
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Moisten batter with a small amount of water as you mix.
Form into small balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli with sour cream dressing
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions or until just tender.
Do not overcook.
While broccoli is cooking, prepare sauce.
Combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan and simmer until butter is melted and sauce is heated thoroughly.
Cooking time is approximately 5 minutes.
Place drained broccoli in serving dish and top with sauce and serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix dates, margarine, sugar and egg.
Add nuts, then mix with Rice Krispies and heat.
When cool enough to handle, shape into balls.
Roll in coconut or sifted powdered sugar.

title: parmesan breaded pork chops
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Beat egg and milk in flat dish.
Dip chops in crumbs, then egg mixture, then again in crumbs.
Melt oleo in baking dish and place chops in dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, turning after first 30 minutes. If chops are thick or not too brown, cook longer.
(To use with 4 chops, reduce crumbs to 2/3 cup.)
Serves 4 to 8.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix well the eggs, sugar and butter.
Add other ingredients and put in unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325°. Makes 3 pies.

title: quick and robust vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine ground chuck and onions in soup pot.
Cook over medium heat until chuck is browned and onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium-low heat for about 15 minutes.
Add extra water, if needed during cooking.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Melt marshmallows over hot water. Stir a little Jello mixture into marshmallows. Blend well and add all remaining Jello. Stir until marshmallows are completely melted. Cool until slightly thickened. Fold in pineapple, cream cheese and whipped cream. Pour into mold or serving bowl. Serve on lettuce leaves with salad dressing.

title: taco rice skillet
directions: Cook rice and tomato juice for 20 minutes. Brown hamburger, onions and salt. Add to rice. Also 1/2 package taco seasoning. Put in oven. Then put shredded cheese on top about 15 minutes before serving. Put lettuce on top of everything just before serving. Do not heat after lettuce is on top.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg; stir with fork.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Spread with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut into 1-inch widths.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Makes 1 dozen good sized rolls.

title: five layer cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix in flour and sugar. Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add to peanut butter mixture.
Pour into jelly roll pan or an 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Spray pan with Pam or grease and flour.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: golden scones
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly combine flour, bran, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture is size of coarse bread crumbs. Stir in raisins. Thoroughly blend 1/2 cup milk with egg.
Gradually add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead 10 to 12 times.
Pat into a circle 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 8 wedges.
Arrange on cookie sheet. Combine milk with brown sugar and brush on surface of scones. Shape into cone shape. Bake at 350° approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: danish red cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage in fine strips.
Sprinkle with vinegar.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add sugar, salt and cabbage and cook 15 minutes.
Stir and add apple and jelly.
Simmer 2 hours, covered; stirring a few times is a must.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crumbs and cover bottom of 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Line the side of pan with ladyfingers (or cream fingers; cut in half lengthwise).
Combine both cheese cake mixes, softened cream cheese and 3 cups milk until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into pan and refrigerate 2 hours.
Top with pie filling and serve.

title: bayou shrimp casserole
directions: Add soup to cheese; heat.
Be careful not to burn cheese. Saute onions and garlic in butter; add to cheese mixture.
Add rice and broccoli to mixture; gently stir.
Add shrimp.
Top with crumbs.
Heat at 300° until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine flour, butter or margarine and regular sugar.
Rub between hands.
Press into cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread evenly onto crust.
Pour pie filling on the top and refrigerate.

title: veggie chili
directions: Saute onion, garlic and veggies until soft in 1/4 cup olive oil in a 2-quart pot on medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients with enough water to cover, plus 1-inch more.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Heat oil very hot.
Add rice and fry for 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in all remaining ingredients.

title: sweet tater pie
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, salt, ginger and cloves.
Mix in eggs and milk.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Add the boiling water; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add the slightly beaten egg yolks, into which a little of the mixture is blended.
Simmer for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Blend in the lemon juice, butter and lemon rind.
Turn cooled filling into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup herb stuffing.
Bake about 40 minutes at 375°.

title: golden onion rings
directions: Mix flour, salt, egg, milk and oil.
Cut onions 1/4-inch thick and separate.
Dip into batter and deep-fry until golden brown.

title: a good cake with sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix and pudding mix.
Add eggs, water, oil and preserves, beating as you add each.
Beat well.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour in tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: daddy's delight
directions: Step 1 - Crust:
Mix 2 cups flour with 1 cup melted margarine. Stir in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook and chop chicken.
Cook pasta in chicken broth and drain.
Place both in a large dish.
Saute onions, peppers, and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add soup and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add hot sauce.
Pour mixture over chicken and pasta.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cherry chocolate pie
directions: Drain cherries; reserve juice and chop cherries.
There should be 1/4 cup juice and 1/3 cup cherries.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, using cherry juice and milk to make amount of liquid called for.
Cool.
Pour into cooled pastry shell.
Chill.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix fruit well together.
Stir lightly so as not to mash fruit.
Add sliced bananas and chopped nuts.
Blend gently together.
Add marshmallows and blend in Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight and serve.
Will fill a 9 x 13-inch glass cake dish.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: orange-lemon tea fizz
directions: In teapot, pour water over tea bag; brew 4 minutes and remove tea bag.
Pour into pitcher and stir in sugar, lemon, orange juice and soda.
Serve over ice and garnish with orange slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bread
directions: Melt butter in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle yeast on butter.
Place biscuits around sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: sangria cruz
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve iced.

title: pizza roust
directions: You will need 1 pie tin.

title: church social yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat butter, egg and sugar. Add flour, salt and boiling water; mix well.
Refrigerate dough overnight or until well chilled.

title: taco cups
directions: Prepare cooked hamburger with taco seasoning mix as directed on package.
Spray nonstick cooking spray on a 12 cupcake pan. Line each cup with a crescent roll (just enough to cover bottom). Layer meat mixture, taco sauce, Cheddar cheese and crushed Doritos.
Bake at 375° until crescent rolls are browned and cheese melted.
Let set 3 to 5 minutes after done.
Remove from pan.
Top with lettuce, sour cream and tomatoes.
Make ahead and freeze.

title: cool citrus punch
directions: A day or two ahead, prepare an ice ring by freezing orange and/or lemon slices in a circular mold. Just before serving, empty cans of thawed concentrates into a large punch bowl. Stir to mix them thoroughly. Pour in the soda and add the ice ring.

title: going bananas
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add oil and mix.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Add bananas and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° in 2 bread pans.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and gelatin in saucepan over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook mixture just to boiling; pour over popcorn until completed coated.
Butter hands and form into balls. Cool on wax paper.
Makes 12 to 18 balls.

title: easy squares
directions: Cream oleo at medium speed.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
At low speed, add flour and vanilla.
Spread batter on greased cookie sheet (jelly roll pan).

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Stir soup until creamy.
Add milk, cheese, onions, uncooked macaroni and dried beef.
Fold in hard-cooked eggs.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled and baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Light brown sugar may be substituted for dark brown sugar.

title: bean pot for a crowd
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown beef over medium heat.
Drain off fat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and ketchup; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into a large kettle or roasting pan.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ingrid's mediterranean sea
directions: Drain tomatoes; save 1/4 cup juice.
Throw tomatoes, juices and all the rest of the stuff in a bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon of artichoke marinade and mix it all up.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups salsa.
Serve it over omelets, chicken, seafood or whatever.

title: chicken pizzarella
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, heat oil.
Add onion, mushrooms, garlic and oregano.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until onion is soft.
Stir in tomato sauce and pepper.
Place chicken in 2-quart baking dish; cover with sauce. Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes.
Put Mozzarella on top and continue baking 5 more minutes or until cheese is bubbling.

title: applesauce torte
directions: Mix brown sugar and Fluffo together first.
When well mixed, add remaining ingredients except applesauce and cinnamon.
Grease pan; line bottom of pan with 3/4 crumb mixture.
Spread applesauce evenly over top; add the sprinkles of cinnamon.
Add remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sausage and cabbage shelled
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 20 minutes or until done. Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: 5 minute steak sandwiches
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Toast bread on one side in broiler.
Spread untoasted sides with 1 tablespoon melted butter and mustard.
Completely cover with meat mixture.
Spread 1 tablespoon melted butter over top.
Broil.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Mix the sugar, apples and Crisco. Sift flour; add to apple mixture.
Flour the nuts and add with spices and preserves.
It is best to put the dry ingredients in the flour and sift. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Beat Crisco, 1 1/2 cups granulated sugar and eggs in with an electric mixer until fluffy, then add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt which have been sifted together and stir into Crisco mixture.
Shape dough into balls.
Roll in 3 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon, mixed together.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger, bacon and onion together, then drain fat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot 3 to 4 hours or 1 hour at 350° in oven.

title: watermelon rind sweet pickles
directions: Remove all the green outer rind and all the red meat from the melon, leaving only the white rind.
Cut into squares or strips about 3/4 to 1-inch thick.
Cover with brine made by mixing salt with 3 quarts of cold water.
Add ice cubes.
Let stand 5 or 6 hours or overnight.

title: burnt sugar crunch sauce
directions: Heat sugar in a 12-inch heavy skillet, over medium heat until sugar begins to melt.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until turns amber in color, stirring constantly.
Add boiling water slowly.
Stir in oleo until well blended.
Cook until thick, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool 10 minutes.
Stir in cream and vanilla. Refrigerate several hours.
Sauce thickens as it cools.
Spoon over ice cream and top with toffee.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and add oil and sugar; mix well.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Add dry ingredients and stir again.
Fold vanilla and nuts in.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 medium loaves.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press evenly onto bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and set aside to cool.
Mix pineapple, creamed cheese and nuts well.
Add coffee cream and cooled jello.
Mix well.
Pour into individual molds or large flat dish.

title: pineapple sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in cooking oil, then add salt, pepper and beef bouillon.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes, then add green pepper, onion and pineapple chunks.
Blend sugar, pineapple syrup, vinegar, cornstarch and soy sauce together and add to mixture.
Cook, stirring often for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: coffee crumb cake
directions: Follow directions on the box.
Put into 11 x 14-inch, 1 1/2 to 2-inch deep.
Bake as directed on box.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar;
add
eggs and beat well. Add graham
cracker
crumbs
and milk; beat until smooth, add vanilla. Fold
in coconut and pineapple;
pour into oiled pan and bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed on package with milk. Add Eagle Brand milk, then fold in Cool Whip. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture, ending with pudding. Makes one extra large bowl of pudding.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine ingredients in medium casserole dish and bake in oven at 350° until warm.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Do not peel.
Cut into thin slices.
Put cucumbers, onions and pepper in large container.
Dissolve salt in water and pour over vegetables.
Stir.
Put a 2 inch layer of ice on top and let stand 3 hours.
Weight them down with heavy object. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in saucepan and bring to boil. Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Drain vegetables and add syrup. Bring to a hard boil and remove from heat at once.
Pack in jars. Fill to overflowing and seal at once.
Store in cool, dark place. For best flavor, chill before serving.
Makes 6 pints.

title: hamburger-potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until just tender.
Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain. Mix together soup, milk and salt. Add to hamburger.
Layer hamburger with sliced potatoes in large casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Pour margarine in a 9-inch baking pan.
Mix flour and sugar in a bowl.
Slowly add milk and stir.
Pour over melted margarine, but do not stir.
Spoon pie filling over batter and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
To serve, top with whipped topping.

title: june's blueberry salad
directions: Using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan - Mix pie filling and pineapple, including juice, right in the pan.

title: my mama's sweet taters
directions: Combine ingredients in a greased pan and bake in oven or to one side of the grill or on top of the stove at a very low heat until hot and flavors are blended.

title: easy salsa raviolis
directions: Cook ravioli according to package and drain well.
put in shallow casserole in layer with salsa.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or in microwave 3 to 5 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour together; bring to a boil in saucepan.
Add jello; remove mixture from heat.
Add cherries and let cool.
After the mixture has cooled, add the bananas and nuts. Pour into baked pie shells and chill.
After pies have chilled for about an hour, top with whipped cream.
Makes 3 pies.

title: cooked play dough(kids stuff)
directions: Take boxes of spinach out of freezer.
Place in pot.
Boil for 6 hours.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown chops on both sides; place in shallow baking dish. Lightly mix together bread cubes, onions, butter, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup water; pour over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: pistachio ambrosia
directions: In a large bowl, mix both types of pineapple and sprinkle pudding on top. Let it sit for a few minutes. Add nuts and coconut and then fold in whipped topping and marshmallows. Refrigerate for a minimum of 2 hours before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together
all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips, and
place	in
baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top. When ready to	put
in
oven,	cover
top
with crushed potato chips.	Bake until heated through, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: suzie's strawberry pie
directions: Simmer 1 cup strawberries with 2/3 cup water for 3 minutes. Blend sugar, cornstarch and 1/3 cup water; add this mixture to strawberries.
After this starts to boil, continue boiling for 1 minute (or until thick), stirring constantly.
Add a few drops of red food coloring if desired.
Cool.
Spread cream cheese over crust.
Put well drained strawberries on top of cream cheese.
Pour cooked mixture over berries.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: black and white meringue
directions: One hour before baking put whites in bowl room temp.
Heat oven 250 degrees.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, put cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges with juice.
Mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jellos and water; cool.
Put rest of ingredients through a food chopper.
Add to jello mixture and chill.

title: sheer delight
directions: Stir all together.
Serve after 1 hour's refrigeration.
Serves 12 or more.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° until done.
This is moist and easy to store.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onions in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in taco sauce, beans and 1 cup of the cheese.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted. Pour into serving dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top in a ring.
Serve with your favorite chip.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly. Bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Just before serving, mix in slices of Velveeta cheese and let melt. (Use as much cheese as desired).

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour cake batter into pan and bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.
Let cool. Mix together the cream cheese, milk and instant pudding.
Spread over cooled cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with desired cake toppings.
Refrigerate.

title: jean's wine cake
directions: Mix the cake and pudding, adding oil and sherry. Mix in eggs, one at a time, adding nutmeg at the last. Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and let cool. Sprinkle powdered sugar over top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender and take chicken off bones. Mix Pepperidge stuffing with 1 stick of melted margarine and half the broth. Pat 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of 9 x 12 baking dish and save remaining for topping.

title: pecan pie i
directions: Add eggs, 1 at a time, to sugar and beat thoroughly after each addition.
Add pecans, salt, vanilla and Karo syrup.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: garden chicken
directions: Saute bacon; remove and put in baking dish.
Saute celery and onion; put in dish over bacon.
Add drained mushrooms.
Saute chicken strips and put over vegetables.
Put red potatoes over chicken.
Pour tomatoes over all; cover and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients lightly.
Add flour, baking soda and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 to 3-inches apart (they spread out during baking).
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes.

title: mike's mexican salsa
directions: Finely chop onions and tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Divide thawed dough in half; roll and stretch each half into 10 to 12-inch circle on round pizza pan. Turn up edges 1/2 inch and pinch.
Brush circles with oil. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Mix tomato sauce, onion, salt, oregano and garlic powder.
Pour on circles.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Decorate with overlapping pepperoni slices, green pepper strips and olive slices for face.
Bake until crust is brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cut chicken into pieces for frying.
Melt butter in hot frying pan.
Add chicken and cook 10 minutes.
Add liver and gizzards and cook 10 minutes longer.
Add onions, curry, salt, wine and enough boiling water to cover.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to platter.
Thicken the liquid in which chicken was cooked and pour this sauce over chicken.
Serve with a border of rice.

title: juicy turkey breast
directions: Rub turkey with oil and sprinkle with sage and paprika.
Place onion and garlic powder in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place turkey on onion.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour apple juice over turkey and cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 2 hours or cook 20 minutes per pound.

title: sausage omelet
directions: Heat sausage in heavy 8-inch ovenproof skillet according to package directions.
Remove sausage and keep warm.
Saute onion and green pepper in same skillet over medium-high heat until vegetables are tender.
Combine eggs and milk in medium bowl.
Add onion, green pepper and tomato.
Melt butter in same skillet over low heat.
Add egg mixture and cook until eggs are almost set. Arrange sausage on top of eggs.
To finish cooking top of omelet, broil, 4 inches form heat, until center is firm and top is lightly browned.
Cut into wedges and serve immediately.

title: milwaukee sandwich
directions: Butter two slices of bread.
Trim off crusts.
Place a slice of chicken meat on one piece of bread.
Sprinkle with Roquefort cheese.
Season with paprika.
Cover with the other slice; toast on both sides.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve hot.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Let cool.
Mix in lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Take bag of nachos and crumble into salad. Pour bottle of dressing over salad and mix.

title: guru cookies
directions: Melt chocolate with peanut butter in double boiler or in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows. Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan; chill.
Cut into squares.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Saute garlic in 1/4 cup butter.
Remove garlic; saute mushrooms.
Combine spinach, onion and remaining 1/4 cup melted butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
With this mixture, cover the bottom of a 10-inch shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Cover with mushrooms, then remaining cheese. Refrigerate, if desired.

title: cranberry pineorange jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; stir well.
Add fruits with the juices; mix well.
Chill until set.
