This is excellent served with the Thanksgiving turkey.

title: butter coconut cake
directions: Mix all together, except coconut, blending cake until mixed well.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Bake at 375° in angel food pan until done.

title: microwave texas brownies
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a large bowl.
In microwave-safe dish, combine butter, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over flour mixture, stir and add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Pour in 9 x 11-inch pan dish.
Microwave at Medium-high for 18 minutes, turning dish every 4 to 5 minutes until done.
(May look soft on surface.)
Top with Chocolate or Caramel Frosting.

title: pretzel salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt butter and add sugar and pretzel crumbs. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and bake about an hour in a 350° oven.
Mixture will be soupy at first.

title: chocolate bourbon balls
directions: Microwave margarine in medium bowl on High, 1 to 2 minutes. Mix in sugar, nuts and bourbon. Refrigerate until firm. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and refrigerate until firm.
Combine chocolate morsels and cream in a small bowl.
Microwave at Medium-high 1 to 2 minutes, stirring once.
Chocolate should be melted.
Stir until smooth and drizzle over bourbon balls. Chill.

title: corn dog
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add wet.
Mix well.
Dip wieners in batter and fry in hot deep oil until cooked.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken in salt water.
Remove chicken and all but 1 quart of broth.
Bone and dice meat.
Set aside.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat eggs 1 minute.
Add sugar, then oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top or serve with whipped cream.
Cut in squares.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Melt butter in double boiler; add flour, salt and pepper and stir.
Slowly add milk and stir until sauce thickens.
Cut cheese into cubes; add to sauce.
Stir constantly until cheese melts.
Pour cheese sauce over macaroni. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thoroughly mixed and sugar is dissolved.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes after mixture begins to boil or candy thermometer reaches 235° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until browned on top.
Yields 5 dozen small balls.

title: scrumptious chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend well with mixer until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press 1/2 of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs over filling.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.
Yields about 3 dozen bars.

title: groovy butter cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick butter.
Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, then beat 2 eggs, 1 stick butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Spread on top of crust and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Cover with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cold german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins.
In a bowl, add green onions (all), chopped onion and peeled potatoes.
Pour salad oil over mixture.
Cover and let it stand 2 hours.
Stir about every 30 minutes.

title: frito pie
directions: Heat chili beans in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
In casserole pan, put Fritos.
Add chili beans.
Shred Cheddar cheese over the chili beans and Fritos.
Put in oven and heat until cheese is melted.

title: creamy crab dip
directions: Drain and slice crab.
Blend sour cream with horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Add crab and chill.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls out flat on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, dry dressing mix, and mayonnaise.
Spread mixture on cool crescent roll base.
Sprinkle with veggies (any combination can be used) and pat to set veggies firmly in mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese and pineapple.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Form the mixture into a ball.
Roll in crushed pecans.
Refrigerate.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: true french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar with a top and shake until blended.
Store in a cool place and shake before pouring over salad.
As served on the ship "The France."
Delicious!

title: cabbage and ground turkey
directions: In a heavy 3-quart pot brown the ground turkey, drain fat and return to pot.
Add onion, cabbage and seasoning.
Cover and begin cooking at high heat, then reduce to medium heat, stirring until completely done to keep cabbage from scorching.
Allow to cook in its own juice.
You may add water if needed to keep from sticking. Add only 1/2 cup at a time.
This is much better when cooked in its own juice.

title: microwave peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, and salt in 1 1/2 qt. dish.
Add milk gradually, mixing well. Cook, uncovered, in microwave 7-8 minutes on high, or until thick, stir occasionally.
Beat a small amount of mixture into egg yolk.
Return mixture to dish.
Cook 2-3 minutes more, or until thick.
Add vanilla and butter and stir well.
Cool filling to room temperature.
Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar (about 3/4 c. total) until crumbly.
Layer peanut butter mix, pudding mix, repeat.
Top with meringue or whipped topping.

title: molasses snaps
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Mix dry ingredients and stir in raisins and nuts, if used.
Stir flour mixture into molasses mixture.
Drop dough from a teaspoon onto a lightly greased baking sheet, space cookies about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set but not hard.
Remove from baking sheet while warm.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Saute garlic and onion in butter.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Put mushrooms in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve as appetizer or vegetable side dish.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Bring to a boil all the ingredients and simmer 10 minutes. Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: chocolate-toffee caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Combine cake mix, oil and eggs.
Blend well.
Stir in chips and candy bars.
Mixture will be thick.
Press 1/2 of cake mixture into greased pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: mixed bean soup
directions: Soak beans in 2 quarts of water overnight.
Cook beans until almost tender, then add all the other ingredients.
Cook on low until well done.

title: crock-pot pork
directions: Salt and pepper the pork.
Place pork in crock-pot.
Add vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook on medium to high heat for four hours or until tender.

title: carrot cake(9 servings)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon well.
Add carrots, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix briskly with fork until thoroughly blended.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and walnuts.
Pour in 9-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool.
Spread with frosting.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Beat until well mixed.
Mix in dry ingredients, mixing well after each ingredient.
Add pumpkin and nuts; mix well.
Pour into 2 large, well-greased loaf pans.
Cook 75 minutes; cool before removing from pans.
Freezes well.

title: chicken-rice pilaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except soyameat and paprika.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cut soyameat into strips and press down into rice mixture.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Mix and stir in dry ingredients. Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix oleo and sugar; add eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk; add cocoa.
Batter will be thin.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 3 well greased and floured 9-inch pans.

title: dijon pork chops
directions: In mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, oil, pepper and parsley flakes; mix well and set aside.
Spread both sides of pork chops with mustard; then press pork chops into bread crumb mixture, coating both sides.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Makes 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaves. Freezes real well.

title: hot mustard
directions: Soak mustard in vinegar overnight in airtight container.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add mustard and cook in double boiler until thick.
Stir while cooking.

title: chicken cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, chicken, apple, grapes, celery and walnuts in large bowl; set aside.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Season chops with meat tenderizer and seasoned salt.
Heat enough cooking oil to cover skillet bottom.
Brown chops.
Add rice.
Add water to cover rice and chops.
Cover and simmer until water is absorbed, approximately 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper in 1 1/2 Tbsp. butter until soft. Grease 9 X 13 dish.
Place butter tossed spaghetti on bottom. Cover with sauce. Then add - in order - 1/2 swiss cheese, 1/2 pepperoni, 1/2 mozzarella, all mushrooms, onions, and green pepper.
Sprinkle with the basil and oregano.
Top with remaining pepperoni and cheeses.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserve a few crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Serves 10 to 12.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together and put into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in pan with bacon and onion.
Add beans and rest of ingredients.
Place in crock-pot on high for 2 hours and on low for 2 hours.

title: festive chocolate fudge
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, evaporated milk, marshmallows, butter or margarine and a few grains of salt.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat, until it comes to a boil (mixture will be bubbling all over top).
Boil and stir 5 minutes more. Take off heat.
Add chocolate pieces.
Stir until completely melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread in an 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into 30 pieces.
Butter pan before putting fudge in.

title: fireside coffee mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 3 1/4 cups mix

title: broccoli waldorf salad
directions: In a large serving bowl, combine the first four ingredients. Drizzle dressing, toss to coat.
Refrigerate.

title: "porcupines"
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, onion, green pepper and seasonings. Form into small balls. Fry in hot fat, turning often, until light brown in color. Add tomato sauce and water. Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Melt butter.
Add chopped onion to the butter.
Cook until clear.
Add paprika, pepper, sugar, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and vinegar.
Cut a 3-inch slit in each frank. Place cut side up on flat baking pan.
Pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Baste hot dogs with sauce.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Can use loaf pans, Bundt pan or muffin tins.
It freezes well (wrap in Saran Wrap, then foil).

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of pie plate.
Cover with can of chili, taco sauce and grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, 1 egg and melted margarine.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add 3 eggs and beat, then add powdered sugar.
Pour over patted dough. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
(Add some coconut or nuts if you like.)

title: bagel bites
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and spread 1/4 teaspoon margarine mixture over cut sides of each bagel half. Place bagel halves, cut side up, on a baking sheet; broil 6 inches from heat for 1 minute or until golden brown. Yields 4 halves.

title: apricots with yogurt
directions: Spoon fruit into individual servings dishes.
Blend remaining ingredients and spoon over fruit.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: creamed broccoli soup
directions: Cover broccoli and onion with water; cook together in large pot (Dutch oven) until tender.
Add salt.
Add margarine.
Blend milk and flour.
Blend slowly into cooked vegetable pot, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and rinse.
Add butter, milk and Velveeta.
Pour into large casserole.
Lay cheese slices ornately over top.
Bake in oven until cheese slices are brown and bubbly.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add flavors.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well (use high speed with electric mixer). Sift
the flour
and salt together, then add slowly.	Fold in coconut.
Pour into
10-inch
stem
pan
that
has been well-greased
and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill 1 hour.

title: caramel brownie tarts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place mini-foil or paper baking cups in 3 miniature cupcake tins (36).
Heat butter in a medium bowl with mixer until creamy.
On low speed, beat in sugar, eggs, melted chocolate, vanilla and salt.
Gradually beat in flour.
Divide batter into baking cups using 1 level tablespoonful per cup.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until barely done.
Press one candy, bottom side up, into the center of each tart until even with top.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from tins and cool. Makes 36.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Sprinkle beef with flour mixed with the salt, pepper and paprika.
Toss with oil in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, stirring once.
Add vegetables; pour in tomato sauce and water.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: mustacietto cookies
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Add sugar and beat, then add flour.
The batter will be thick so you will have to switch to a spoon to mix.
Add baking powder with flour.
Put roasted almonds in food processor and chop (but not too fine).
Add nuts and baking chocolate (grated), then whisky or rum.
When all ingredients are mixed, take a couple tablespoons and place on floured board.
Roll with hands to a long hot dog.
Shape, flatten and cut every 2-inches.
Repeat until dough is used.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl combine sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix.
Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with one-third each of the wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding.
Cover and chill.

title: cheesy tuna shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Saute onion in margarine in a medium pan until limp.
Remove from heat and add mushrooms, tuna, dill, celery salt, sour cream and 1 cup cheese.
Mix carefully and set aside.
In a small bowl, mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup cheese, egg, milk and corn.
Stir just to blend.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 9 x 3 1/2-inch pan.
Top with tuna mixture and bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese; return to oven for an additional 30 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring and salt.
Add flour and soda alternately with sour cream.
Beat at low speed until creamy.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry party punch
directions: Combine juices; chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Garnish with orange slices.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream; set aside.
Brown hamburger.
Add salt and tomato juice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread hamburger over noodles.
Top with cream cheese and sour cream cheese mixture.
Cover with sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake for 10 minutes.

title: j. j.'s chili
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven with onions, bell pepper and garlic. Drain fat.
Add soup, beans (with juice), chili powder, vinegar and Tabasco sauce.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 30 minutes. Serve.

title: green bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine milk, soup, soy sauce and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in cooked beans and half of the onions.
Bake for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions and bake for 5 minutes more.
Yields 6 side dish servings.

title: curried fruits
directions: Drain fruits.
Place in greased casserole.
Melt butter; blend in sugar, cornstarch and curry powder.
Spoon curry mixture over fruits.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Melt 1/3 cup chocolate chips and let set.
Mix together and set aside.
Mix all the other ingredients, then add melted chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients into large bowl.
Mix with wire whip until blended.
Sift remaining ingredients in separate bowl.
Add to above mixture, mixing well with wire whip.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Frost with a glaze or leave plain.)

title: pumpkin cheese cake torte
directions: Mix together and firmly press into bottom of glass 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: cheese 'n chive dreams
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the cream cheese with the sour cream; add cottage cheese and mix well (mix by hand, don't use a beater). Add beaten eggs and Bisquick.
Fold in the melted margarine until it is completely mixed.
Drop by teaspoonful into greased mini muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans for 3 or 4 minutes before removing with a spatula.
Great flavor.
Good for a party.

title: turkey stuffing roll-ups
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed.
In a bowl, combine soup and milk.
Spoon about 1/4 cup stuffing into each turkey slice. Roll up and place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over roll-ups.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with onions and bake 5 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: m&m cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended well.
Press down small ball of dough with finger to make a fingerprint on top.
Then add M&M's in the center.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: tastier meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 450° to 500°.
Mix ground chuck, bread and eggs; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in separate bowl. Season to taste.
Set half aside.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 2 well-greased pans. Bake at 400° until done.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in a large saucepan until all red is gone.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, tomatoes, catsup, steak sauce, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix cheese with cooked macaroni until melted.
Combine with beef mixture. Spoon in mushroom soup.
Pour mixture into casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes two 1-quart baking dishes.
Can be made and frozen.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Heat butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in flour, salt, peppers, mustard, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add cheese; cook, stirring occasionally, until melted.
Stir in remaining macaroni gently.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: kielbasa and chicken gumbo
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook bacon until crisp; remove. Drain and crumble on paper toweling; set aside. Cook kielbasa and chicken in hot bacon drippings until chicken is browned. Remove kielbasa and chicken, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings in Dutch oven. Add flour to drippings; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 12 to 15 minutes or until a reddish-brown roux forms. Gradually stir in tomato juice and water. Add tomatoes and bouillon, stirring well. Add kielbasa, chicken, tomato sauce, okra, onion, green pepper, bay leaves, salt, red pepper and allspice; mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add shrimp and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Remove and discard bay leaves. Stir in file powder and bacon; mix well. Serve over hot cooked rice, if desired.

title: low-fat veggie pasta
directions: Combine cooked vegetables and butter until butter is melted. Add Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and pasta; toss gently to mix. May serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in saucepan and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Then remove saucepan from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture out on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Let cool.
Ready to eat.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs and spices, then cream, soda and flour. Add the jam last. Bake in greased pan about 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine flour and seasonings.
Pound into meat.
In a skillet, brown meat in shortening; pour off fat.
Add soup and ketchup.

title: simple potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Drain and mash.
Add onion, pickle, mustard and Miracle Whip.
Chop 2 eggs.
Add to mix.
Mix well. Garnish with 2 eggs.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: Cover beef with water and boil about 20 minutes.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: scalded hush puppies
directions: Pour enough boiling water into the meal to make a sticky dough. Drop by small spoonfuls in hot grease. These are quick to brown and are so crisp and different. Makes good "hors d'oeuvres".

title: sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on low heat for about 30 to 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix in bowl the flour, salt and sugar. Set aside. Bring to boil the Coke, margarine and cocoa. Remove from heat and add marshmallows. Then add buttermilk with the soda in it.
Add the flour mixture and the two well-beaten eggs and mix.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
Add 1 cup peanut butter.
Stir well.
Pour quickly into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch buttered dish.
Sets up quickly.

title: pear jam
directions: Grind fruit and measure 3/4 cup sugar for each cup of fruit. Let stand overnight.
Cook until thick and seal in pint jar.

title: herb-butter sauce for grilled steak
directions: Put butter/margarine in small bowl and allow to come to room temperature until soft.
Beat with a wooden spoon until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice, pepper, parsley, tarragon and Tabasco. Thoroughly blend.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with cracker crumbs.
Spread soft ice cream over crumbs.
Place soft bananas over ice cream.
Pour on chocolate syrup, then spread on whipped cream.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.
Freeze for at least 1 hour and allow to sit in fridge for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: never fail cheese souffle
directions: Butter bread and cut off crusts.
Shred cheese.
In bottom of greased, deep casserole dish, place 3 slices of bread.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese
over.
Repeat with 3 more slices of bread and rest of grated cheese.
In blender, put milk, eggs, salt and dry mustard.
Blend.
Pour liquid over bread and cheese
and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: walnut chicken salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken salad, chopped walnuts, mustard and tarragon; mix well.
Cut each cantaloupe quarter lengthwise into 4 slices.
Arrange 4 slices on each of 4 spinach-lined plates. Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto each plate next to cantaloupe slices.
Garnish with walnut halves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix everything together and pour over pretzels.
Stir to coat. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.

title: easy chocolate truffles
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar, beating until well blended.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well. Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Roll in walnuts, cocoa or coconut and place in muffin liners.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chinese wedding cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Beat together drained pineapple, cream cheese, pudding mix and milk.
Spread on top of cooled cake. Top with a layer of Cool Whip, then sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: vegi casserole
directions: Mix together corn, green beans, mushroom soup, onion, sour cream and shredded cheese and pour into casserole dish.
Mix together crackers, margarine and almonds and put on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten out the rolls on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes until brown. Cool and cut into squares, bite size.

title: broccoli pie casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add broccoli.
Cook until thawed and cool.
Add rice and Cheez Whiz.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole dish, except fried onion rings. Cook (bake) in 350° oven approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Season to taste with black pepper.
Add onion rings last 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan combine sugars, salt and milk.
Cook to 240° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows and peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat several minutes until thick and creamy.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares. Makes 48 pieces.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook until brown in 3 tablespoons of butter the burger and onion.
Add beans and tomato sauce.
Cook 10 minutes.
Make a paste of chili powder, flour, salt, soy sauce and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
May add a clove of garlic.

title: mabel and minnie's carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture and mix well.
Add carrots, pecans, pineapple, coconut, vanilla and orange rind.
Pour into a greased and floured large size tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cinnamon sugar syrup
directions: Combine ingredients in 1-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil, shaking pan gently until sugar dissolves, then boil, without stirring, until thick and syrupy for 8 to 10 minutes.
Discard cinnamon stick and store in jar with screw top.
Store in refrigerator and shake well before using (or warm in microwave). Yields 2 cups.

title: barbecued hamburger(american heart association recipe)
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large skillet.
Pour off the fat. Add all ingredients and mix well.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.
Spoon into hamburger buns.
Yields 6 (1/2 cup) servings.
Calories per serving:
200 (320 with bun).

title: macaroni salad
directions: Season with Accent, Lawry's salt-free lemon pepper (small amount) and garlic powder (if desired).
Mix well.
Add enough Miracle Whip or mayonnaise to moisten.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix well by hand in large bowl.
Roll into balls the size of a small walnut.
Place on the cookie sheet about 2 1/2 inches apart. Do not flatten!
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 350° oven until tested done.

title: mahogany glazed chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine all the ingredients, except the chicken.
Bring to a boil and cook about 4 minutes.
Remove the pan from the heat.
Place the chicken on a rack and baste with the mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for at least 45 minutes or until cooked.
Baste every 10 minutes.
Pour the remaining sauce over the chicken and serve.
Serves 6.

title: peggy's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into hot, greased pan.
To prevent sticking, sprinkle bottom of pan with cornmeal.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: coney slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Stir in mustard until mixture is a bright yellow.
Add sugar and vinegar and stir well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
You may make it sweeter or tangier by adding more sugar or vinegar.
Store in glass or plastic container (never use metal bowl).
Keeps in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: international dinner
directions: Line up the dishes in order.
Allow each guest to serve their own plate.

title: italian broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the broccoli, onion, water chestnuts and mushrooms. Pour dressing over vegetables; toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Add tomatoes; gently toss. Yield: 9 servings.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Cook on medium heat until smooth.
Pour over meatballs; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt sally's poppy seed loaf and glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients 1 to 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together all but last 2 ingredients.
Add walnuts and apples.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes.

title: pear blueberry crisp
directions: Make sure your pears are peeled, cored and sliced.

title: working woman's dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread undrained pineapple in pan. Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake powder over fruit.
Dot with slices of margarine.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crumble all cookies, except 4, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread softened ice cream over cookie crumbs.
Next, layer hot fudge over ice cream.
Then, spread Cool Whip over fudge.
Crumble 4 remaining cookies and sprinkle over the top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix ingredients together in a heavy saucepan.
Cook to soft-ball stage.
Beat until creamy.
The candy will turn cloudy. Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Lightly toast English muffin halves.
Spread each piece with sauce.
Place on paper plate.
Let children add toppings of their own choice.
Microwave on plate for 45 to 60 seconds, or until cheese is melted.
Or place cookie sheet under broiler just until cheese is melted instead!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together and add other ingredients. Chill dough and then roll in balls and dip in sugar and flatten. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine oats, sugar, flour and nuts.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbled.
Pour 1/2 mixture in bottom of 8-inch greased baking pan.
Spoon pie filling over crumbs.
Place remaining crumbs over filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cajun barbecue shrimp
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour over raw shrimp.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Place shrimp with marinade in roaster.
Add butter and wine.
Stir and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
For large shrimp, bake 25 minutes, but don't overcook.
Serve shrimp in bowls with liquid.
You'll need 2 napkins, one for your hands and the other for wiping your forehead.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix apples and margarine.
Add next 4 ingredients to apples. Combine the brown sugar and flour.
Cut into margarine; add nuts. Sprinkle over apples. Place in a 9-inch pie or cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise in food processor.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients except for crab meat and mix well.
Fold in crab meat.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: boston lettuce salad
directions: Wash lettuce.
Combine eggs, onion and carrots with lettuce. Mix with Blue cheese dressing.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Prepare cheesecake as directed on box and let chill for 30 minutes.
Wash and trim strawberries, then slice.
Combine strawberries and pie filling; spread on top of cheesecake.

title: blondies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar, stir until well mixed and let cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into oblong pan (10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When almost cool, cut into squares.

title: dill dip for veggies
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: homemade bread butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, bell peppers, garlic and salt in ice water and let soak for 3 hours; drain and cool pack in jars.
Mix remaining ingredients to a good hot boil.
Pour over cucumbers; seal jars. Have a pot of warm water.
Sit jars in hot bath.
Let cook for a full 5 minutes or let water come to a boil, then turn off and let sit for 5 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; add chicken, then grapes.
Cover and refrigerate for a minimum of one hour; stir.
Serve in pita with lettuce.

title: three bean salad
directions: Use equal amounts of onion and tomato slices (looks nice with long thin slices).
Sprinkle generously with salt, pepper and white vinegar.
Chill.

title: minute-quick snacks
directions: Combine all ingredients except fillers in large mixer bowl. Mix at low speed of mixer until a dough forms.
Shape into a firm ball.
Wrap each filler in a teaspoonful of dough, covering completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Step 1:
Dissolve large package of raspberry Jell-O in 3 cups of boiling water.
Pour into large clear dish to set.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt together.
Add boiling water while stirring constantly on high heat, until mixture thickens.
Cook slowly on low heat until thick and add beaten egg yolks.
Cook 2 minutes longer; add lemon juice and rind.
Cool. Pour into a baked pie shell; top with meringue.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars and milk together over low heat.
Pour milk and chocolate mixture with syrup into ice cream freezer.
Stir until mixed.
Enjoy.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, salt and pepper.
Form into small balls and place them in a large baking dish.
Saute pepper and onion in oil and add tomato juice.
Pour over balls and bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Add lots of ice.

title: meat loaf
directions: *Use 1/4 cup of catsup in meat and 1/4 cup for the top of meat.

title: sot suppe(a norwegian cold, fruit soup)
directions: Place tapioca and water in kettle.
Let soak for several hours.
Prepare seedless raisins and prunes as directed on package for stewed fruit.
Remove from burner and cool.
Place kettle of tapioca mixture on burner.
Cook until mixture is almost clear. Add grape juice, lemon juice, sugar and cinnamon. Simmer gently for several minutes or until clear.
Gently stir in stewed fruit. Can be served warm or cold.

title: brussels sprouts scallop
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts according to instructions on bag.
While sprouts are cooking, brown bread crumbs in butter or margarine. Combine mushroom soup with milk and heat.
Drain cooked sprouts and add to mixture.
Turn into baking dish and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until crumbs are brown.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and pepper into a bowl to make a sauce. Arrange potato slices in rows in baking dish with cheese and sauce between each layer.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake for 10 more minutes or until potatoes are tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad for weight watchers
directions: Use pineapple juice to mix pudding mix with Tang.
Mix well and add fruit.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until thick.
Mix the next 4 ingredients well; add flour, cream of tartar, soda and vanilla. Mix and roll thin.
Put a teaspoon of filling between 2 cookies. Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine.
Saute onion.
Add beans and carrots.
Stir until all ingredients are coated with margarine.

title: mexican chicken(polly roach's recipe)
directions: Brown chicken in oil; spoon off fat.
Mix sauce ingredients and pour over chicken (all ingredients except cheese).
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes until chicken tests done. Place chicken in ungreased pan (13 x 9-inch) and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400°, covered, for 10 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead.
If kept longer than 24 hours, freeze.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: davies apple slices
directions: Peel and core apples and slice thicker than pie slices.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and add enough water or cider to make a loose syrup.
Put sliced apples into large shallow baking dish.
Pour syrup over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until apples are soft.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in a casserole dish (2-quart) at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Add a little water if needed. Form into tiny marble sized balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: rolling in dough
directions: Combine roll mix, yeast, sugar and salt.
Melt butter.
Beat egg; add to hot water.
Add to dry ingredients.
Knead until soft; roll into a ball.
Set aside in a warm place; cover with a tea towel.
Let rise for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Punch down; knead a little.
Using hands, break and roll pieces of dough into small balls and place into round, greased cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add milk and butter.
Mix together and cook
minute
after it starts to boil all over.	Remove from heat
and
add
peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop from a spoon onto buttered cookie sheets.	Let harden.

title: cheesy zucchini
directions: Heat skillet with the olive oil and butter.
Add the zucchini and fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute until the zucchini is crisp-tender.
Add the tomato sauce and mix.
Then add the cheese, cover the skillet and allow the cheese to melt.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: diabetic blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. In another bowl, beat margarine, Splenda and honey with electric mixer until fluffy. Beat in eggs (one at a time) and add vanilla. Alternately stir in flour and milk. When blended, fold in berries and spoon batter into paper lined or greased muffin cups. Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, salt, mayonnaise, lemon juice, almonds, onion and chestnuts together.
Place in buttered baking dish and cover mixture with potato chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: minute macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water.
Drain and put in a bowl with the eggs and tuna.
In a second bowl, mix the mayonnaise, mustard, adobo, salt, sugar, black pepper, chopped onion and celery.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook the spinach according to directions, drain and squeeze. Add all other ingredients, mix until well blended.
Refrigerate for a few hours.
Remove and roll into small balls, appetizer size, placing on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and it's ready to serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, drain and mash.
Mix with the white sugar, 1/2 stick margarine, evaporated milk, butter flavoring and eggs.
Mix well and place in casserole dish.

title: hot taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef.
Mix with all but last four ingredients. Cook until thickens.
Put nacho chips on bottom; pour chili on chips, then add the rest, if desired.

title: italian sausage and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thinly slice onion.
Pare potatoes; slice 1/4-inch thick.
Layer potatoes and onion in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Wash green peppers; cut into rings.
Remove seeds.
Arrange on top.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil.
Pour salad oil and 1/2 cup water over the peppers. Arrange sausage on top; cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove foil; bake 1/2 hour longer or until sausages are browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: best ever barbecue
directions: Combine all except turkey; cook over medium heat for about 3 minutes.
Add turkey; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger rolls.
This is a great way to get rid of turkey leftovers.

title: cran-raspberry mold
directions: In a bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add undrained pineapple and cranberry sauce, stirring until cranberry sauce melts. Chill until partially set by placing bowl into a larger bowl of ice water or chill in refrigerator.
Pour half of the gelatin mixture into a 6 1/2 cup ring mold.
Chill until almost firm.
Let remaining gelatin stand at room temperature.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: *To rehydrate mushrooms, cover in hot water for 2 minutes; clean and chop.

title: french garden peas(france)
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until peas are tender, about 8 minutes.

title: soap flakes finger paint
directions: Mix starch with enough cold water to make a paste.
Add boiling water and stir until clear.
Cool and add soap flakes and coloring.
Store in airtight container.

title: popovers
directions: Combine eggs, milk and shortening in mixing bowl; add flour and salt and beat until mixture is smooth.
Pour into hot, greased custard cups or hot iron muffin pans.
(Cups should not be more than 1/2 full.)
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 12 popovers.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until very well creamy.
Add egg and blend.

title: irish soda bread(top o' the morning to ya!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add raisins.
Toss well to coat.
Whisk together buttermilk, eggs and melted butter.
Add buttermilk mixture to flour mixture.
Add caraway seed.
Mix until just blended.
Do not overmix!
Grease pan or ovenproof bowl well.
Bake about 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a small mixing bowl.
Mix in the milk and egg yolks.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in oleo (as for a pie crust), then pour the liquid mixture over it.
Stir just to moisten.
Grease the dough, cover the bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Dough can be refrigerated up to four days.
Allow dough to double in bulk.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface to 1/2-inch thick.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice into 24 slices.
Place on greased cookie sheets. Grease tops and allow to rise.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° until light brown.
Rolls may be frosted with powdered sugar frosting if desired.

title: stuffed salmon fillets
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Make a slit 2/3 of the way through the center of each fillet; do not cut through fillet.
Season each fillet with salt and pepper.
In bowl, combine spinach, pesto, sun-dried tomatoes and pine nuts.
Spoon 1/3 cup mixture into each slit.
Arrange fillets on broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Roast 8 to 10 minutes or until spinach mixture is heated through. Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk; stir dough.
Turn dough out on board; knead until smooth. Roll dough into large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples, then sprinkle apples evenly over the dough. Roll up like a jelly roll.
Dampen edge of dough with water and seal.
Slice dough in about 16 slices 1/2-inch thick.
Place in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around slices. Bake about 1 hour.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and margarine and form into 1-inch balls.
Place on a big cookie sheet and chill for a few minutes.

title: "no-fail pie crust"
directions: Work
shortening into dry ingredients (flour, sugar and salt). Add
well	beaten egg, vinegar and water.	Mix lightly and divide into four parts for 2 large two-crust pies, or into six parts for 3 small two-crust pies.

title: mulled cider
directions: Tie cinnamon sticks, cloves and allspice in a small cheesecloth bag.
Pour cider into a large, heavy enamel kettle, then add bag of spices and brown sugar.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Remove the bag of spices.
Pour cider into a metal or heatproof punch bowl, float lemon slices on top and serve hot. Serves 12.

title: exa's rolls
directions: Heat potato water, milk and shortening.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients, except flour.
Add flour gradually and beat well until about the consistency of thick pancake mix.
Cover bowl and keep in warm place for 1 hour.
After an hour, add enough flour to knead.
Place kneaded dough back into bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Place spoonful of dough into muffin tins and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruity blend
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Cover and process on high until well blended.
Makes 2 servings.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Melt butter in large heavy saucepan.
Add onions, shallots, celery and bell pepper.
Cook 10 minutes until clear.
Add flour; blend well.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add parsley and shrimp.
Cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring often. Add cream, cheese, jalapenos and garlic.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook on low 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Add sauce.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into 6-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: great grandma's soft gingerbread cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, spices and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add syrup.
Blend well.
Add flour mixture and boiling water alternately to creamed mixture.
Stir in eggs and blend well.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: patio chicken
directions: Roll chicken in bread crumbs and seasoning.
Place in baking dish, skin side up, and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce heat to 300°.
Brush chicken with the mayonnaise. Bake for 1 hour.
Holds well in oven.

title: sponge candy
directions: Place Karo, sugar and vinegar in saucepan.
Boil until crystallized or 300°.
Remove from heat; add baking soda and pour into greased pan.
Cool; break up in pieces.

title: poor boy rice
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet. Chop onion and bell pepper. Saute in butter until soft. Add to skillet the mushrooms (undrained), consomme, water and rice. Add garlic powder and pepper to taste. Stir well.
Place in a 400° oven and bake 35 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, water and syrup.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°).
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add raw peanuts and salt and cook to hard crack stage (290°).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir until bubbling stops. Pour on buttered baking sheet.
Spread thin and let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: italian chicken
directions: Flour chicken.
Brown in hot oil.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Save most of drippings and crunchies.
Remove some grease. Put as much garlic as you like in drippings.
Add olives.
Add salt, pepper and sherry wine.
Simmer.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Place condensed milk into bowl and add lemon juice and grated rind.
Stir until thick and add beaten egg yolks.
Mix oleo with wafer crumbs and press firmly into pie plate.
Pour filling into pan over crumbs and top with meringue which has been beaten with the egg whites plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in oven until egg whites are light brown.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Boil sugars and milk until soft ball stage.
Add butter and let stand; cool to lukewarm.
Beat until creamy.

title: erin's favorite drumstick torte
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers, melted butter and Spanish peanuts. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix chopped ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Pour over vegetable mixture, mixing well.
Cover and refrigerate to chill a couple of hours before serving to mix flavors together.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, then blend in eggs.
Stir in 1/2 cup mini semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Pour into a graham cracker pie crust.
Sprinkle with mini semi-sweet chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; cool.
For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients together.
Pour over Crispix and mix well.
Put 1 cup powdered sugar in a paper bag.
Add mixture, then add 1 1/2 cups more powdered sugar.
Shake until well coated.

title: divinity icing or candy
directions: Cook syrup until forms a firm ball.
Add to beaten egg whites.

title: salsa dip
directions: Spread cream cheese over bottom of 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Add the remaining ingredients from bottom to top (in order).
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Melt Velveeta and pour over macaroni, stir.
Pour mixture into cooked, scrambled hamburger; add spaghetti sauce.
Stir together and pour into baking dish (cake pan size).
Place pepperoni on top and sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until top is light brown.
(Can be refrigerated until ready to bake.)

title: spiced pineapple pickups
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple.
Combine 3/4 cup of sugar and vinegar.
Add salt, cloves, remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Heat 10 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks and bring to a boil.
Refrigerate 24 hours; drain and serve with picks.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to mixture; mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: seafoam chews
directions: Cream
shortening, white sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Add all
dry
ingredients
sifted
together.
Add
egg yolks, vanilla and
milk.
Press into 15 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle on chips.
Beat egg whites; add 1 cup brown sugar and beat until stiff; spread over
top sealing it well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana twinkie delight
directions: Cut Twinkies in half the long way.
Layer bottom of bowl with Twinkies.
Cut bananas in slices.
Put over Twinkies.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Then do all this again.
Make a day ahead.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix and pour over boneless chicken or chicken parts. Refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Can be drained and put on grill or put in pan; and pour marinade over chicken and bake in oven.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Braise 1 pound chuck roast (cubed).
Add the chopped onion and celery.
Add 2 cups water.
Slowly cook over medium heat for approximately 2 hours.
Add the chopped cabbage.
Add the tomatoes; cook for 1 hour.
Add the salt and sugar.
Cook 1 hour.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine and pat
into
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: honey lemon chicken
directions: Skin chicken and place in baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour over chicken, turning pieces to coat.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Turn and baste once.

title: veg-all cheesy chowder
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Add flour and whisk or stir in.
Cook on low heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add cheese and seasonings (white pepper and hot sauce), stirring until cheese melts.
Add Veg-All and parsley flakes.
Reduce heat and cook until heated.
Do not boil.
Serve with bread sticks spread with garlic and butter and toasted.

title: devilish piggy wings
directions: In small bowl, mix together butter and hot pepper sauce.
In shallow plate, mix together Cajun seasoning and crumbs.
Dip ribs into butter mixture and then roll in the seasoning mixture.
Place ribs an inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet or other shallow pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, until golden. Serve with Blue cheese dressing for dipping, if desired.
Serves 4. Preparation Time:
10 minutes.
Cooking Time:
45 minutes.

title: mother's spanish rice
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french toast batter
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients.
Beat well by hand.
Yield:
4 slices bread.

title: samami recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Makes 3 rolls in netting.
Bake at 225° for 4 hours.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Add buttermilk and soda; mix well. In a separate container, mix flour with candy, dates and nuts, then add creamed mixture. Bake in greased and floured tube pan 2 1/2 hours at 275 degrees.

title: oatmeal spice cake
directions: Measure all ingredients and
blend
together
on
low
speed 1/2 minute, then 3 minutes on high speed.
Bake
in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: hot pepper sauce
directions: Boil mixture until peppers and onions are done.
Pack in jars and seal.
Yields 8 pints.

title: wham salad
directions: Chop Wham or use food processor.
Add all ingredients and mix. Serve on bed of lettuce or with lettuce in sandwich.

title: banana berry blend
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth.
Serve immediately over ice or in frosted mugs.
Makes 2 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix rice well with other ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes in a buttered baking dish with bread crumbs at the top and bottom.

title: hot cheddar dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn chips, in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Microwave, uncovered, at Medium-high 2 to 3 minutes, stirring 1 or 2 times during cooking.
Serve hot with corn chips.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Tear cake into small pieces and put into the bottom of a pan. Mix pudding and milk until thick and pour over cake.
Mix glaze and condensed milk; pour over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip; garnish with fresh strawberries and refrigerate.

title: debbie's eggs
directions: Butter bread slices one side only.
Place one slice on top of buttered side to make sandwiches. Remove crusts and cut into fourths.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with buttered sandwiches.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over bread.
Cover with grated cheese and crumble sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: linguine with clams
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Drain.
Meanwhile, drain clams; reserve liquid.
Saute garlic in oil; stir in flour and pepper until smooth.
Add liquid.
Cook, stirring until thickened. Add clams.
Heat to serving temperature.
Place linguine in bowl; pour sauce over and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream together sugar, butter or margarine and eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt;
add to creamed mixture with the buttermilk.
Beat until blended.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.
Glaze with confectioners sugar icing.

title: peanut butter whimsies
directions: Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla (liquid and margarine).
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on wax papered cookie sheet and cool.

title: potato waffles
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Combine the fat, riced potatoes and onions.
Add to dry ingredients and beat 1/2 minute.
Bake in hot waffle iron 3 to 4 minutes.
These are very good served with creamed chicken.

title: easy pepper steak
directions: Slice beef into thin strips.
Add 1 tablespoon oil in skillet over medium heat.
Brown beef in 2 batches.
Remove.
Add 1 tablespoon oil.
Add peppers, onions and garlic powder and cook over medium heat until tender-crisp.
Add gravy and Worcestershire.
Return beef to pan.
Serve over rice.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Add nuts or coconut, if desired, after adding peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.

title: potato gratin with boursin cheese
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir cream and cheese in large saucepan over medium heat until melted and smooth. Arrange 1/2 of potatoes in overlapping rows.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over 1/2 of the cheese mixture.
Arrange rest of potatoes; season with salt and pepper and rest of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour until top is golden and potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of taco shells, coarsely broken.
In skillet, brown beef.
Drain and add taco seasoning and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in onion and tomato sauce.
Spoon meat over taco chips.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of cheese over meat.
Top with the rest of the taco chips and then the rest of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Garnish with tomato and olives.

title: barbecued beef clog(boneless beef shoulder)
directions: Sprinkle meat generously with Worcestershire.
Rub meat with Tony's, garlic powder and onion powder.
Place in refrigerator until time for cooking.
Let marinate at least 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Heat pit until coals are glowing; cover with hickory chips which have been soaked in water.
Put meat on rack away from direct heat.
Cook at about 350° (moderate heat) about 3 hours, basting periodically with dressing.
Reduce heat in the pit or bring roast into the conventional oven and finish cooking at 225° two hours longer for the 5 pound roast and 12 hours longer for the 15 to 20 pound clog.
Baste at intervals all through the cooking.

title: homemade enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and olives.
Heat enchilada sauce and Ro-Tel.
In a long pan, lay a shell flat, add meat and sprinkle cheese and then sauce.
Roll up shell and start with another one.
Repeat until pan is full.
Add remaining cheese, then add remaining sauce to top.
Cook at 350° until cheese melts. Serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground round.
Add onion and pepper; cook on low for 5 minutes.
Combine with next 6 ingredients.
Cook in pressure cooker for 5 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.* Add kidney beans; heat until beans are warmed.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix well. Make three wells and put oil in one, vinegar in another and vanilla in the last.
Mix well with one cup water.
Then pour in the second cup and mix thoroughly until bubbles form.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until it looks like coarse cornmeal. Add salt.
Add water a little at a time until with a fork all is moistened.

title: vena's meatballs
directions: In frying pan, saute vegetable oil, garlic and onion.
Add tomato paste or tomato puree and simmer.
Add meatballs and simmer about 1/2 hour more.

title: quick caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, stir over low heat.
Add brown sugar, cook for 2 minutes.
Add milk, bring to full boil.
Cool to lukewarm without stirring.
Add confectioners sugar, beat until smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: owen's rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Kellogg's Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.
Yields 24 squares.

title: cream of wheat pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto a lightly greased griddle or skillet.
Cook until light brown on both sides.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat the Dream Whip, 1 cup milk and vanilla until thickened and mixture forms peaks.
Add the pudding and 1 3/4 cups milk. Whip about 2 minutes, then add a handful of coconut.
Sprinkle toasted coconut on top.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions. In large bowl combine tortellini and remaining ingredients. Extra dressing may need to be added after pasta sits for a while.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.

title: custard
directions: Beat sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla and nutmeg together.
Then add milk.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake slow at 350°.
Put knife in middle, if it comes out clean, it's done.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: The chicken can be marinated in soy sauce with a little nutmeg, salt and pepper.

title: 7 calorie pita chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Split pitas and cut each half into 6 wedges.
Mix and crumble herbs and paprika.
Spray pitas with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle on herbs.
Bake 8 minutes or until lightly toasted.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and water.
Cook until mixture forms
soft ball in cold water.
Take from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and butter.
Stir until mixture starts to harden.
Add nuts.
Pour in pan greased with butter.
Cool.

title: crunchy apple crisp
directions: Place filling in quart buttered baking dish.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, salt and spices.
Add butter; mix well.
Spread on filling.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: killer brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Mix sugar and beat in eggs.
Mix and add flour and vanilla.
Stir in marshmallows, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chocolate chips on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spicy pickles
directions: Drain liquid from dills; discard.
Add sugar and Tabasco. Stir.
Cover and let sit 24 hours, then refrigerate.

title: poor man's filet mignon
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients.
Shape into 6 thick patties. Wrap a bacon slice around the sides of each patty.
Secure with a toothpick.
Bake on a rack at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Baste with additional A.1. sauce during the last 30 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a large container.
Place cucumbers and onions into canning jars.
Pour mixture over to cover them.
Place in refrigerator for two weeks, until they are ready.

title: orange salad(or dessert)
directions: Mix well and chill for at least one hour.

title: crab soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots in butter, until soft (not browned).
Add half and half and Cheddar cheese soup.
Stir until combined.
Add sherry and Tabasco sauce.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly warmed.
Add crab meat; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with fresh parsley.

title: vegetarian vegetable soup
directions: Place raw ingredients in a 5-quart kettle and cover with salt and peppered water.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and corn (these make the soup) and heat through.
Serve with a sandwich for lunch or a first course at dinner.

title: carol's simple fruit mold
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: cauliflower mountain(microwave recipe)
directions: Trim cauliflower, but do not cut up.
Place in a shallow, microwavable dish and add 2 tablespoons water.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook for 8 minutes on full power, rotating halfway through cycle.
Mix mayonnaise (can use light mayonnaise) and mustards. Spread over entire surface of cauliflower.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Return to the microwave, uncovered, and heat for 1 minute on full power.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pennsylvania dutch peach (apple) pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut in butter until crumbled.
Slice peaches in wedges.
Arrange peaches in shell. Put crumbled mixture on fruit and bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Change oven setting to 350° and open oven door until oven comes on again and bake there for 32 minutes.
Cool before serving as it will become more firm than coming out of the oven.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Don't drain pineapple.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes a very moist cake.

title: garlic beef roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a glass pie pan or casserole pan. No water, no cover.
Take the roast and cover it good with salt and garlic.
Put in glass dish.
Bake 1 hour, then shut oven off.
Do not open door.
Let sit there another hour.
Serve sliced thin.

title: jello salad
directions: Set cream cheese out to soften.
Make your choice of jello and add 1 cup boiling water.
Stir well and add 1/2 cup cold water.
Refrigerate jello until slightly set.
Add cream cheese and whip until frothy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Can add well drained fruit or make same kind of jello or 2 kinds of jello in cake pans, cube and fold in.
Recipe can be doubled for layer salad.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening, add sugars and cream well.
Add eggs and hot water; beat.
Add dry ingredients, nuts, chocolate chips and oatmeal; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 5 dozen cookies.

title: polly's bread pudding
directions: Looks fabulous and tastes delicious. Well worth the effort. Serves 10 to 12.

title: crunchy peanut cole slaw
directions: Toss the green and red cabbage, celery and cauliflower together and chill in plastic bag.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, salt, vinegar, cucumber, green onion and green pepper for the salad dressing and chill thoroughly.
Melt butter in small skillet; add chopped peanuts and heat until lightly browned.
Remove from the heat and immediately stir in the Parmesan cheese.
Set aside to cool.
Just before serving, toss chilled vegetables with the dressing and top with the peanut mixture.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on size of pan.
Cool before frosting or cutting.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together. Alternately add milk and dry ingredients, blending after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Bake at 325° in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan for 1 hour and 10 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches and cut into 1/4 or 1/6 size.
Put into a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Mix remaining sugar, milk, flour, butter and vanilla in a blender.
Pour mix on top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is light brown and crust is fully baked.

title: great strawberry shortcake
directions: Make cake per directions in 2 layers.
When layers are cool, punch holes in both layers with a 2-prong fork.
Leave 4 strawberries whole; cut remaining berries into 4ths or 8ths; add sugar and a little water to mix well.
Spread 1/2 strawberries over bottom layer; add top layer cake and spread the remaining cut up strawberries over top layer.
Beat thawed Cool Whip with mixer until it can be spread over entire cake.
Garnish top with 4 whole strawberries that have been cut into halves.
Refrigerate cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together and pour into 9-inch pie pan lined
with
pastry.
Bake until set and pastry is nicely browned. Cool.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Serve cold or slightly warm.

title: chimichangas
directions: Combine garlic, onion, tomato and cumin in bowl.
Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in pan.
Add tomato mixture; cook over medium heat 3 minutes.
Lower heat; simmer 7 minutes, uncovered. Strain mixture with chicken, chilies and salt.
Heat flour tortillas in microwave.
In center of flour tortilla, place teaspoon of mixture.
Fold ends of tortilla together; place in frying pan.
Fry until brown.
Turn sides of tortilla.
Put tortillas on plates and serve.

title: tomato filled squash
directions: Cook squash in boiling salted water for 5 minutes or until tender and drain.
Halve squash lengthwise and scoop out pulp. Combine pulp with green pepper, onions, tomatoes, bacon, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spoon filling into squash cavities.
Top each with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: After cooking spaghetti, drain. Saute onion and pepper in oil. Add remaining ingredients and heat in a heavy pan until cheese melts. Pour into a casserole dish and top with cheese or bread crumbs. Heat at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Add apple, raisins, coconut, pecans and carrots.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat eggs slightly in a separate bowl. Add oil and vanilla to eggs; beat well.
Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients and combine quickly.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 18 muffins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, onion and margarine as pack directs.
Add soup, rice, milk and cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Set oven for 350°.
Melt butter and chocolate together over hot water.
Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar while heating. Add chocolate and butter to egg mixture; beat for 1 minute.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt; stir into egg mixture.
Add walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Bake 40 minutes.

title: lite fruit dip
directions: Blend all of the ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with assorted chunks of fruit.

title: easy bake chicken with gravy
directions: *Or use 2 cans cream of chicken soup.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Fry the bacon in an electric skillet or frying pan until crisp, remove bacon and leave drippings. Drain on paper towel and crumble bacon. Separate onion rings and cook in bacon drippings until brown. Stir in the dry ingredients and vinegar, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add beans and bacon and cook in an electric skillet for 2-3 hours or in a casserole in the oven at 325°f. 160°c. gas mark 3 for 2-3 hours.

title: sausage stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, combine sausage, onion and green pepper. Cook over medium heat until sausage is brown and onion is tender. Drain off pan drippings.
Combine tomatoes, sour cream, water, sugar and seasonings.
Stir into sausage mixture.
Stir in noodles.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: italian spaghetti(makes 200 plates)
directions: Brown meat.
Saute onions, pepper and garlic in butter.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, parsley, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, oregano and paprika.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water and butter.
Drain well.
Combine sauce.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until thoroughly cooked.
Cover bottom of an oblong pan with Doritos.
Mix soups and tomatoes in a separate bowl.
Cover Doritos with shredded chicken.
Pour soup mix over chicken and chips.
Lay slices of cheese over that.
Cook at 350° until cheese begins to turn brown.
Let cool.

title: goodin' puddin'
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Put in cranberries.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar; add nuts.
In a bowl, beat eggs; add 1 cup sugar, flour and melted shortening.
Pour over cranberry layer.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: slaw
directions: Chop.
Pour vinegar mixture over cabbage mixture and stir well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let stand at least 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes.
In a 5-quart pan, bring about 2-inches water to a boil; add potatoes.
Cover and boil until tender throughout when pierced (about 40 minutes).
Drain, then mash well.
In small bowl of electric mixer, beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth; gradually add to potatoes, beating until smoothly blended.
Beat in garlic salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into a buttered shallow 3 or 4-quart casserole.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover with lid or foil.
At this point, you may refrigerate for up to 3 days; bring to room temperature before baking.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven until heated through (50 to 60 minutes).
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large bowl; add eggs and buttermilk, stirring until blended.
Stir in butter and vanilla, and pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Cool on wire rack.

title: orange-loaf cake(original from alberta b. seitz)
directions: Remove seeds from orange; grind or blend orange (peel and all) and raisins.
Mix all ingredients; place in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: texas sugar coated pecans
directions: Beat sugar and salt into egg whites.
Stir in pecans and spread on a cookie sheet (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 200° or 225° for 1 hour.

title: turkey and cornbread casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir all ingredients except bread mix together.
Pour into 10-inch casserole and level.
Prepare cornbreead mix according to directions on package.
Pour over turkey mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: For best results, chill soda and milk before mixing.
Pour in ice cream maker and freeze according to directions.
Add strawberries minutes before ice cream is done.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat, add rest of ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 14-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bacon cheese roll-ups
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Cut each bread slice in half.
Spread bread with cream cheese dip.
Lay bread on 1/2 slice bacon and roll, securing with a toothpick.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or desired crispness of bread.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a greased casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
Perfect side dish with baked ham.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening, then add milk. Roll out on floured board. Bake 12-15 minutes in 425° oven.

title: farm cheese
directions: Add all this and mix.
Put into top of double boiler where 1 teaspoon of butter has been melted.
Stir while it all blends and melts together.
Pour into pie dish; cool and slice.
Serve on bread or crackers.

title: pumpkin ice cream
directions: Mix together all ingredients except gingersnaps.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with gingersnaps.
Add ice cream mixture.
Top with layer of crushed gingersnaps.
Freeze.
Cut into squares to serve. Serves 24.

title: chop suey dish
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off fat.
Saute onions.
In 2 quarts water, break up in small pieces the 1 cup spaghetti with 1 teaspoon salt and boil until done; drain spaghetti.
Add beef, onions, spaghetti, tomato soup, water and grated cheese.
Bake slowly at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: harris cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to sugar mixture.
