Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, then vanilla and beat 2 more minutes.
Will make 3 (9-inch) layers or a loaf cake.
Pour into pans that have waxed paper cut to fit and that have been greased and floured.

title: strawberry lemonade
directions: Wash figs and cut up all you have to prepare.
Measure 1 cup sugar to each 2 cups of figs.
Add 1 box strawberry jello to each 4 cups of figs.
Cook on low heat until figs and mixture come to boil; cook at boiling stage for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool and store in sterilized jars and lids.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine the Jell-O with the hot water.
Mix in the 7-Up.
When partially jelled, add the apples, marshmallows, pineapple, oranges, bananas and 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
When set top with the pudding mixed with milk.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Spread over salad.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into medium pieces and cook until tender crisp. Mix with tomato and green onions.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream butter and sugar, add vanilla, eggs and oats.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture. Pour into greased and floured baking dish.

title: wacky devil's food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine liquid ingredients and then pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Combine honey, oil, corn syrup and vanilla in saucepan. Bring to
a
boil.
Remove from heat.
Meanwhile, mix together oats, Rice Krispies, pecans, almonds, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Pour
honey
mixture over oat mixture.
Mix well. Spread on baking sheet.
Bake
at
for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes,
until
nicely browned.
If desired, add 1/2 cup raisins
after baking.
Store in airtight container.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first nine ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 - 20 minutes or until vegetable are crisp-tender.
Add the pasta and tomatoes; heat through.
Discard bay leaf before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain the spaghetti.
Add the butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Mix and put into a 10-inch shell pan.
Cover with the cottage cheese.
Cook and drain the grease from the ground beef. Add the onion.
Puree the tomatoes with the sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Mix the ground beef and onion with the tomato mixture and pour onto the cottage cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes or until melted.

title: banana coconut cream pie
directions: Dissolve
cornstarch in water in heavy pan.
Stir in milk and egg yolks, cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly and fold in coconut.
Slice bananas and dip in lemon juice, drain. Arrange slices on bottom of pie crust and pour filling over bananas.
Cover and chill for 4 hours or until set.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with coconut and sliced bananas.

title: christmas salad(4 layers)
directions: Let set and add Second Layer.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail (except cherries, save for top) with marshmallows and add sour cream.
Fold in 1 cup walnuts and put in serving dish.
Place remaining walnuts and cherries on top. Refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.

title: black forest cherry cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions. Prepare 2 (9-inch) cakes.
Cool on wire rack.
Drain cherries, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice.
Sprinkle juice over one layer of cake.
Spread with pie filling.
Place remaining layer on top. Spread whipped cream over top and sides.
Decorate with cherries and chocolate curls.

title: red pepper chicken pilaf
directions: Melt butter and oil in large skillet over medium high heat. Add peppers and garlic and saut until peppers are tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove peppers from skillet and transfer to bowl. Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Lightly and evenly coat chicken with flour.
Place chicken in skillet and saut until light brown, about 4 minutes per side.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Place peppers back in skillet, adding broth and cooking wine. Cook on high for 5 minutes until thick.
As sauce thickens, scrape up browned bits.
Return
chicken to skillet until no longer pink in center. Add salt and pepper.
Place chicken and peppers on platter; sprinkle with fresh parsley.
Serve over rice; cut chicken in pieces.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix and knead 49 times. Roll out and cut or drop by spoon into muffin cup. Bake at 425° until done. Makes 6 rolls or biscuits.

title: old time egg pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs; add flavoring.
Put milk and butter in pan; bring to boil.
Pour hot mixture over egg mixture; stir well. Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: hawaiian pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed. Bake in a large tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem strawberries.
Crush 1/2 of them and combine with 1 cup sugar in which 3 tablespoons cornstarch has been mixed.
Stir constantly over low heat until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and allow to cool.
Put the other half of the strawberries into a cooked 9-inch pie shell and top with the strawberry mixture.
Chill and serve with Cool Whip.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Roll on floured board.
Cut in desired shape 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pennsylvania dutch milk pie
directions: Put flour and sugar into unbaked pie shell.
Mix together first and spread over shell with fingers.
Cover with milk and top with butter.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put cider and cranberry juice in bottom part of 8-cup percolator.
Put the remainder ingredients in top basket.
Perk. Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
In top of a double boiler, melt wax and semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Keep hot. Roll mixture between hands into balls.
Lift balls into hot chocolate mixture to be coated. Remove and place on wax paper on pan. Place in refrigerator to remain firm and hard until ready to serve.
Makes 50 or more.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream cheese pecan cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2
cup
pecans in a greased and floured tube pan. Set
aside.
Cream
butter
and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
well
after each addition.
Add flour and salt, stirring until
combined.
Beat until light.
Stir in vanilla and remaining 1 cup pecans.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 325° for
1/2 hours
or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on wire rack.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cranberry freeze salad
directions: Cream together well the cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar. Add well drained pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Add a few drops of red food coloring as desired.
Freeze well.
Thaw 15 minutes before serving on a bed of lettuce.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt.
Beat well and add chocolate chips.
Add the vanilla and vinegar to the water.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, sugar, cocoa, the vanilla, vinegar and water mixture, salt, baking soda and oil.
Mix and beat well.
Fill cupcake papers 1/2 full of chocolate mixture.
In middle of each, put heaping tablespoonful of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place sliced apples in an 8 x 11-inch greased Pyrex dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour 1 cup water over apples.
In a separate bowl, mix flour and sugar together.
Then add margarine. Mix well until crumbly.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave cashew crunch
directions: Line a cookie sheet with lightly greased foil.
Have a greased spatula ready.
Mix sugar and corn syrup in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart glass measure.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes until sugar dissolves and mixture is bubbling.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard and sugar to make the dressing and set aside.
Shred head of cabbage and mix with onions.
Pour dressing over cabbage and onions and chill.

title: honey-apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and 1/4 cup honey. Combine dry ingredients and add to honey mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla, nuts and apples.
Mix gently and pour into a lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Combine margarine, brown sugar, milk and remaining honey in saucepan.
Boil and cook over medium heat 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook noodles using package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine noodles, shrimp, celery, onion and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Chill for 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.

title: dippity dogs
directions: Prepare pancake mix as directed on package for 7 - 8 pancakes.
Stir in salt, pepper, and paprika.
Dip wieners into batter then drop into deep oil heated to 375 degrees.
Fry until golden brown, 2 minutes.
Insert skewers lengthwise into wieners and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wedding salad
directions: Mix and chill 24 hours.
(Two batches makes one 5 quart ice cream bucket full.)
Marshmallows and coconut optional.

title: tuna cheese biscuit casserole
directions: Place biscuits in an ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Combine the other ingredients together and pour over the top of the biscuits (biscuits will rise to the top).
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Gradually add milk, beating.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into pie shell.
Chill before serving.

title: tomato french dressing
directions: May be blended in blender.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with 12 graham crackers (whole).
Mix and bring to a boil the sugar, 1/2 cup Pet milk and 2 sticks melted butter.
Pull away from heat and add nuts, coconut and crushed graham crackers.
Spread over crackers.
Place 12 crackers on top of mixture.
(Make sure the crackers are placed in same direction as crackers on bottom.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except dressing.
Line casserole with herb dressing (butter if desired).
Add squash mixture.
Cover with herb dressing.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix together.
Put 3 teaspoons in cup.
Add hot water and stir.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil together.
Put rest of ingredients together.
Put in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet cook sausage until browned; drain off fat. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes then Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(A piece of foil underneath will protect oven.)
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Heat bacon drippings in heavy skillet.
Add flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until light brown.
Add tomatoes and liquid.
Add salt to taste.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil 2 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add dry jello and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add strawberries and pineapple. Refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: moroccan lentil stew
directions: Put package of lentils in a large pot and cover with water. Add potatoes and carrots if desired.
Add salt; cover and cook 20 minutes.
Then saute chopped onion in oil with chopped tomatoes. Add ginger, turmeric and black pepper and continue to cook until onion is translucent and spices are well mixed.
Add this mixture to the cooked lentils and continue to simmer the stew gently for another 20 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix crab with butter and cream cheese. Add the rest of the ingredients. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: grand marnier carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into strips lengthwise.
Cook in boiling water with lid on until tender.
Drain and remove to greased 7 x 9-inch shallow baking dish.
Melt butter and stir in flour.
Cook for 1 minute.
Gradually add orange juice, stirring constantly until mixture bubbles.
Add Grand Marnier.
Blend well and remove from heat.
Pour evenly over carrots.
Garnish with twisted orange slices that have been halved.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding(usa)
directions: Line dish with vanilla wafers.
Slice bananas.
Put into dish. Mix other ingredients and put over the wafers.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar.
Pour over rhubarb in pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry cake roll
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs with vanilla until fluffy and light colored.
Gradually beat in granulated sugar.
Stir in water.
Fold in sifted dry ingredients, carefully but thoroughly.
Turn into waxed paper lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until done.
Sift confectioners sugar evenly onto smooth dish towel. Turn hot cake on towel; carefully peel off paper.
Roll up cake from end, jelly roll fashion; cool.
Add fresh strawberries to ice cream.
Unroll cake and spread ice cream mixture.
Re-roll, wrap in foil and freeze.
Thaw 10 minutes and serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and milk.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Place cheese in small mixer bowl.
Let stand at room temperature until softened.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce and wine; blend on low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy, scraping side and bottom of bowl.
Cover; chill at least 8 hours. Shape mixture into a large ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Place on serving plate, cover and chill for at least 2 hours.
Arrange crackers around cheese ball.
Serve as a spread.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Add salt and let stand overnight in large pan.
Squeeze dry in jelly bag in morning.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Cook 25 minutes.
Take off fire and stir in mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix this while hot, let cool and put in small jars. Put paraffin and lids on the ones you won't use immediately.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add sugar to oil, the add eggs, pumpkin, spices, sifted flour and last of all the water.
Mix Well.
Makes 5 small loaves. Grease tins.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: a happy home recipe
directions: Thoroughly mix love and forgiveness.
Stir in tenderness, loyalty and friendship.
Add friendship, hope and faith.
Sprinkle with laughter.
Bake it in sunshine and serve daily.

title: pineapple pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together after draining pineapple.
Pour into 2 small vanilla wafer crusts or 2 graham cracker crusts. Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: scrumptious chili
directions: Wash beans and soak in water overnight.
Simmer in covered pot for 2 to 3 hours (until tender). Simmer in same water.
Add stewed tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes. Saute garlic, onions and green peppers in 1 tablespoon oil for 15 minutes.
Add to bean mixture. Brown beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add to bean mixture.
Add seasonings and simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Remove cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes more.

title: can't eat just one piece rum cake
directions: In large bowl mix cake and pudding mix.
Stir in oil, butter, 1/2 cup rum, nuts and eggs.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Take out of oven and pour topping over hot cake.
Let stand 3 hours before removing from pan.

title: squash dressing
directions: Boil
and drain
squash.
Cook	meat
to
light
brown. Saute celery, bell pepper,
onion and parsley in 1/2 cup oleo. Cut eggs into small pieces.	Wet and crumble bread.	Add milk; if mixture is not real moist, add water.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour
into
greased baking pan; sprinkle top with bread crumbs and	dot
top
with remaining oleo.	Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cashews; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours or more.
Add cashews before serving.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
May garnish with sliced black olives, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: versatile oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a medium size mixing bowl.
Blend well. Beat milk, oil and egg together and add to dry ingredients; mix.
You can add chopped nuts, raisins, chopped apples, mashed bananas or any fruit to these. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and add eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Mix and add nuts.
(Do not whip or beat.)
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until bread tests done.

title: creamed cabbage(microwave)
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in milk.
Combine all ingredients in 2-quart microwave-proof casserole dish.
Cover.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes or until tender, stirring once during cooking time.
Stir and let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: honey glazed munch mix
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine popcorn, cereal and peanuts.
Set aside.
In a 2-cup microwave-safe dish, melt margarine, honey and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir quickly into popcorn mixture to coat.
Microwave for 6 minutes or until popcorn is crisp, stirring every 2 minutes. Spread onto foil and cool completely.
Store in loosely covered container.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together oatmeal, crushed Shredded Wheat and all-bran cereal. Pour 1 cup boiling water over cereal. Add oil. Add brown sugar and buttermilk. Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to cereal mixture. Fill muffin tin 1/2 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yield: 4 to 4 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on package and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still hot, make holes with fork.
Mix milk and cream of coconut together and pour over hot cake.
Let cool, then top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: green chili-chicken-cheese enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in shortening until soft (a couple of seconds on each side) or don't fry to cut down on fat.
Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put a little more than 1/4 of mixture on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Fill tortillas with cheese and roll. Place in pan.
Pour remaining mixture, covering enchiladas.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, milk, lemon juice, chili powder and salt.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Spread dip evenly on large plate.
In layers, sprinkle onion, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Dip with tortilla chips. Serves 6.
It's delicious!

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni per instructions on box.
Combine other ingredients and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in pan, boil for 3 minutes sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Remove from heat.
Stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: blueberry stack cake
directions: In a large bowl, add all ingredients to cake mix.
Beat until well mixed. Bake in 6 thin layers.
Ice with filling.

title: red plum cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over cake after removed from pan.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreos up in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass cake pan. Flatten Oreos.
Cover with vanilla ice cream; smooth out completely, covering Oreos.
Put into freezer at least 1 hour. Cook sugar, German chocolate, butter and Pet milk.
Cook to boil stage; boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and cool. Pour over ice cream.
Cover with Cool Whip; sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Freeze.

title: tom's venison steak with onions
directions: Roll steaks
in
flour
seasoned
with salt and pepper. Heat oil in
heavy skillet.
Brown meat on both sides.
Remove from pan.
Saute onions until limp, but not brown. Add steaks, mushrooms, water
and
bouillon
to
skillet. Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 hour.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix all, adding enough flour to make a soft dough.
Chill until firm.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Space about 1/2-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 7 to 9 minutes.
Roll immediately in sugar.

title: brandied hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and add next 5 ingredients; add cream and vanilla. Bring to boil, then simmer 5 minutes or longer. Pour in jar (approximately 2 cups).

title: cherry pudding dessert
directions: Make pudding per instructions on box, less one cup of milk. Shake and mix in closed container.
Let pudding stand for at least 5 minutes to thicken.

title: hot shot potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Dump into bowl with hash
browns. Mix mushroom soup, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add soup, sour cream and mayonnaise mixture to potato mixture; salt and pepper to taste.
Top with 2 cups crushed Rice Krispies tossed with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gourmet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Add mixture to remaining ingredients and toss.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and water together. Mix dry ingredients well and add to egg yolk and water mixture. Cook in

a bowl in the microwave on High until thick, stirring occasionally. Cool until center is cool, stirring often. Pour into a baked pie crust and top with meringue. Brown the meringue in a slow oven about 325° until lightly brown. Cook pie crust alone before adding filling at 400° until brown.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well and pat into a ball.
Place in bowl and refrigerate until chilled and easy to handle.
Roll in sliced almonds to cover.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Thaw and cook broccoli and place in greased casserole.
Place chicken (or turkey) on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, water chestnuts and pimiento and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Top with bread crumbs/butter mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes or until browned.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons drippings from saucepan.
Add onions and brown a bit.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook, covered, about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Blend in chicken soup, milk and salt. Heat but do not boil.

title: green beans
directions: Stem and cut beans.
Cook in water.
Not enough to cover them. Fry bacon (after dicing) until crisp.
Pour off most of grease. Add to beans, cook about 1 hour or until beans are done.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon; stir well.
Pour into baking dish and top with bacon slices.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in airtight container. Use 1/4 cup mixture in 6 ounces hot water for a great cup of hot chocolate. Great for camping.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix and bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Eat with Wheat Thins.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix all other ingredients well and chill.

title: creamy lemon pie(makes one 8 or 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand, ReaLemon and food coloring (if desired).
Pour into prepared pastry shell; bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice cooked potatoes when warm.
Cool.
Add eggs, onions and pickles.
Add 3 to 4 serving spoonfuls of salad dressing to start. Add 3 good squirts of mustard.
Sprinkle celery salt, salt and pepper over top of mixture.
Mix together.
Season to taste. Garnish with paprika.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in bowl.
Heat oleo, cocoa and cola until boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add milk, eggs, soda and vanilla and beat well.
Add marshmallows.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: fruit fool
directions: Combine pie filling and whipped topping.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
If desired, sprinkle each with coconut and/or garnish with mint.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Once chicken and spaghetti are cooked, allow chicken to cool and chop into small pieces.
Mix cheese and Ro-Tel and heat until cheese is melted.
Saute onion, bell pepper and mushrooms. They can be sauteed in the 1 stick of butter or for healthier preference, simply use vegetable oil spray to prevent sticking while sauteing.
Place cooked spaghetti in casserole dish and arrange chicken pieces over top.
Mix remaining ingredients, vegetables, cheese sauce and Worcestershire sauce together.
Pour over the top of chicken and spaghetti.
Then pour 1 cup of reserved broth from the chicken over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: applesauce tart
directions: Mix together oats, flour, brown sugar and salt.
Blend in melted butter.
Press 3/4 cup mixture into bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Fill with applesauce and top with remaining oat mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
This was my great grandmother's recipe.

title: pie pockets
directions: Cook and dice 4 chicken breasts.
Cook and drain all vegetables.

title: hedge hogs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Cool slightly.
Roll in balls.
Then roll them in coconut and powdered sugar.

title: quick pie crust for fried or baked pie
directions: Cut flour and Crisco together to make look like corn meal. Add water, a little at a time, just to wet all so it sticks together.
Make small balls to make into 6-inch circle.
Roll out. Place 2 tablespoons of fruit of your choice.
Fold in 1/2 moon shape.
Close with fork; press around edges.
Fry in oil in skillet or bake at 375° on greased sheet until brown.

title: crab meat-scallop casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, folding in egg slices at end.
Butter and cube 3 slices of bread and sprinkle on top of sauce, using a 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yum!

title: stuff chicken
directions: Prepare chicken for stuffing, removing all bones and meat, leaving skin, wings and legs intact.
Soak in lemon juice and soy sauce.
Chop meat of chicken.
Mix ground pork and chopped chicken, then add ham, sweet relish, hot dog, eggs, cheese, raisins, peas, ketchup, cornstarch, pimientos, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix them all together.
Stuff chicken with meat mixture.
Sew up opening and bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of pie plate. Place remaining ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate. Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Serves 6.

title: chicken in red wine
directions: Heat olive oil in a skillet.
Add garlic, briefly.
Slice mushrooms and cut tomato into chunks; add to skillet and saute 2 or 3 minutes.
Add wine, lemon juice and chicken breasts.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes, turning chicken once.
When chicken is done, remove it and vegetables from pan.
Turn heat to high and reduce sauce.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.

title: irish soda bread(8 to 10 loaves)
directions: Sift together the flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking powder and sugar (as flour is usually measured in pounds, start with 8 cups and, depending on density and humidity, use up to 10 cups).
When thoroughly blended, add raisins and mix through the flour.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Boil together all ingredients, except beans.
Wash beans under cold running water.
Drain.
Pour cooled mixture over beans. Refrigerate 12 hours or more.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato-chicken
directions: Skin the chicken.
Remove the meat from the bones.
Cut meat into chunks (4 to 5 chunks from each leg).
Remove skin from each ginger.
Cut ginger into 4 to 5 slices.
Press 4 to 5 cloves of garlic flat.
Mix garlic, oil and ginger.
Deep fry for about 5 seconds on medium heat.
Add chicken and bones to vegetable mix. Continue frying on medium heat for 10 seconds.
Turn to high heat. Add wine.
Saute for 5 seconds.
Add water.
Heat until water boils.
Turn heat to low for 8 minutes.
Add salt, soy sauce and potatoes.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Remove bones.
Serve.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer
bread cubes, then sausage, then cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.	Bake
at
350°	for
minutes.
Serves
to 8 people.
Great for holiday breakfast.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo to hard boil stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cooked syrup, beating constantly.
Beat until you can drop from a spoon (the candy that is).

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Drop by teaspoons onto greased (or Pam sprayed) cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to cool 4 to 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: cooper salad
directions: Blend cheese, mayonnaise and milk.
Add juice, sugar, oranges, cherries and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream and spoon into paper baking cups.
Freeze in muffin tins.
Makes 18.

title: stew
directions: Brown ground beef; cook rice.
In a large pot add this and all other ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: sue's good brownies
directions: Melt margarine; beat with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Grease 9 or 10-inch baking dish.
Combine all ingredients until zucchini is just coated.
Add a little extra Cheddar and Parmesan cheese on top, if desired, before putting it in the oven. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: spiced fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, measuring juice.
Add water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add juice mixture.
Measure 2 1/4 cups of gelatin juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend remaining gelatin slowly into cream cheese.
Add cinnamon and beat until smooth; set aside.
Add fruit cocktail to thickened gelatin.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Chill until set, but not firm (15 minutes).
Top with cream cheese mixture. Chill until firm (3 hours).
Makes 10 servings.

title: surprise tuna pie
directions: Spread tuna in bottom of pie crust with diced cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt. Pour over tuna and cheese. Bake 20 or 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat broth.
Make a paste of cornstarch and water. Add sugar, salt and pepper. Stir in cornstarch mixture. Cook and stir until slightly thick.
Holding eggs above the pot, pour in slowly, constantly stirring to break into strings.
Serve with noodles. May top with chopped green onions.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and lemon juice, mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: grandma campbell's baked pineapple
directions: Beat all together; break up 5 slices of bread and add to the ingredients.
Add 1 can crushed pineapple.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pink panther salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for Cool Whip.
After other ingredients are mixed well, then add Cool Whip.
Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: nancy's pink punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; add 50-50 pop last, don't stir. Before serving, put in sherbet; float on top.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 350 degree oven for about 45 minutes.
If potatoes are not thawed it may take a little longer.

title: german lasagna
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the noodles, eggs, milk and salt together.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the mixture, alternating with the noodles.
Mix and pour over eggs, milk and salt.
Bake in 350° (oven) for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix together and spread in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until light brown.
Let sit a few minutes before serving.
Freezes well.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, butter and pecans.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs, sugar and pecans. Pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Continue beating and add vanilla and flour.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet.
Using a spatula, mark batter into about 20 squares.
Put a heaping tablespoonful of cherry pie filling in the center of each square.
Bake at 350° until done (will not be very brown).
Cool slightly, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Finish cooling; cut into squares.
(Can also serve warm.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, eggs, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts and chocolate chips. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Split cake in 2 halves.
Remove a few chunks from bottom half. Place strawberries in bottom half.
Add some of the Cool Whip to berries.
Place top half of cake on Cool Whip and berries.
Put chunks, removed from bottom half, in center of cake.
Ice entire cake with Cool Whip.
Place in freezer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Prepare pudding as directed substituting pineapple juice for milk.
Cook and let cool.
Add pineapple chunks, bananas and cherries.
Refrigerate and serve when chilled.

title: muddy buddies(a.k.a. "puppy chow")
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl.
Set aside.
In 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over cereal until pieces are evenly coated.
Pour mixture into resealable bag with powdered sugar and shake until all pieces are covered.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed, except use orange juice concentrate in place of water as directed on cake mix box.
Add drained pineapple and pecans, if desired.
Bake in layers or sheet cake pan.
Bake as directed on cake mix box.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Arrange in this order in a punch bowl:
crumble half of cake, 1 can pie filling, 1/2 can pineapple, 1 can pudding and 1 tub Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Top with whipped cream Cool Whip droplets, maraschino cherries and chopped walnuts, if desired.
Chill before serving.
Serves 30 to 35 people.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in vanilla, flour and nuts. Chill.
Shape dough into balls about an inch in size.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool about 5 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: old-fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix corn, milk, salt and pepper. Beat in eggs and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until firm.

title: crustless crab spinach quiche
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13 dish at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: one cup cookies
directions: Blend sugars, margarine and egg.
Add oil and vanilla.
Beat well so oil does not separate.
Add dry ingredients to flour and stir into batter.
Chill for 1/2 an hour.
Then, form into balls and flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
My favorite cookie!

title: granola bars
directions: In a 3-quart pan, melt butter, then add brown sugar, honey, vanilla and salt; stir until well blended.
Stir in granola and desired nuts and coconut.
Turn into a well-greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Press in firmly to form an even layer.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven until browned and bubbly, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into bars while still warm.
Yields 32 bars.

title: french settlement jambalaya
directions: In a large electric skillet or Dutch oven, brown thinly sliced sausage.
Put aside.
Brown chicken pieces that have been seasoned with salt and pepper in the same drippings.
Put aside.
In the same drippings, saute onions, garlic, bell pepper and raw rice about 5 minutes.
Add chicken bouillon, tomato sauce and all spices.
Stir well.
Return chicken and sausage to pot.
Cover and cook on low flame until rice is tender (add water as necessary). Serves 6.

title: spicy peach pickles
directions: Drain syrup from peaches into saucepan.
Add spices and vinegar.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over peaches; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve as relish with meats.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Save syrup after peaches are served.
Heat and pour over more peaches.

title: dumplings for chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in hot soup until dough comes clean from bowl.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Add to hot soup and bring to a boil.
Turn fire out, let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: party punch
directions: Chill juices and Mountain Dew.
Pour into a punch bowl.
Add sherbet, gently, into bowl with a large spoon.
